#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:122
msgid "Optional First Player Bidding in Doomsday"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:124 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:128
msgid ""
"Machine Scenarios: The DM starts the game as first player and will bid "
"when appropriate. The DM bid is resolved after human players have "
"completed their Econ Phases. The DM only bids if a DM is on the board. If"
" a Human player wins the bid, they may determine player order as normal. "
"While the DM is first player the Human Players may decide and commit to "
"their own play order during each Econ Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:125 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:129
msgid ""
"Bid Amount: The DM bids the lower of 2d10 but gets these CP for free. If "
"both die result in the same number, add this number to the result of "
"another lower of 2d10 (these die rolls “explode”). If doubles again, "
"repeat this again but this is the final result."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:135
msgid "Gameplay Advice"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:137
msgid ""
"The play time for this game is in the 1 to 4-hour range for a solitaire "
"game, depending on the scenario. For cooperative games, the play time "
"will be at the higher end of that range, even if the players are "
"experienced. Since new players tend to take longer the first couple of "
"times they play any game, here are some suggestions to keep play time "
"down in the early games."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:138
msgid ""
"• Start with just the basic rules. While they are fairly simple, the game"
" offers a lot of choices and decisions. Starting with just the basic "
"rules simplifies some of the choices and makes the first few Economic "
"Phases easier to wrap your head around."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:139
msgid ""
"• Start with the 1-Player Small Doomsday Machine Scenario (2.7). This is "
"the least complex solitaire scenario, and it will allow you to become "
"accustomed to the feel of playing against the game before introducing "
"Alien players or trying cooperative games."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:140
msgid "• Be aggressive! This is a game that rewards aggressive play."
msgstr ""

