msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:293 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1661
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1686
msgid "Movement Guidelines"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:295
msgid "DMs always move towards the"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:296
msgid ""
"closest player Colony. If two Colonies are equidistant, then a DM will "
"always move toward the Colony that is larger (in CP). If more than one "
"equidistant Colonies are the same size, then the DM will move towards the"
" Colony that brings it closest to the player’s Homeworld. If it is still "
"tied, then it is the player’s choice. As a DM moves toward a Colony, if "
"two different hexes will put it equidistant from the target Colony, it "
"will move toward the hex that is also closer to the player’s Homeworld. "
"Each time a DM moves, its target Colony may change. The player may not "
"reduce a Colony or remove it in order to change the direction of a DM."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:302 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2759
msgid "Strength and Weaknesses"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:304
msgid "Each map contains a table"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:305
msgid ""
"indicating what Economic Phase each DM enters play and the DM Rating row "
"to use for that DM’s statistics (Table 2.5). When DMs enter play, roll "
"1d10. The DM appears in the matching red-numbered hex on the scenario "
"map. When that DM is first encountered, its weakness is determined by "
"rolling a die and consulting the Doomsday Machine Weakness Table (2.6)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:311 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2768
msgid "Movement Rate"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:313 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2770
msgid "DMs always move one hex per turn and"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:314
msgid ""
"may not use Warp Points (MRB 28.2). Unlike in multiplayer games, DMs can "
"move in a hex with an unexplored marker and when it does, do NOT flip the"
" marker."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:320
msgid "System Markers and DMs"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:322
msgid "DMs are unaffected by"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:323
msgid ""
"System markers (see exceptions in 2.3.7 and 2.3.8). A player may not move"
" into a hex with a DM and an unexplored System marker. If you wanted to "
"move there you should have explored it before the DM got there!"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:329
msgid "Special Combat Conditions"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:331 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:337
msgid "A DM’s Attack/Defense"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:332 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:338
msgid ""
"Strengths are not affected by Asteroids or Nebulae. DMs are affected by "
"Ion Storms (MRB 25.1.3) and Quasars (MRB 5.8)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:333
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 5"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:334
msgid ""
"Unlike multiplayer games, DMs do not destroy Asteroids in solitaire "
"scenarios (MRB 29.4)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:344 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2831
msgid "Planets and Colonies"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:346
msgid "If a DM is in a hex with a planet"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:347
msgid ""
"(with or without a Colony), it will destroy that planet. Remove the "
"planet and any Colony from play. The DM must first defeat any defending "
"ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:353
msgid "Doomsday Machine Combat Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:355
msgid ""
"• If a DM moves into a hex with the player’s ships, it will engage them "
"in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:356
msgid ""
"• Unless specified as a weakness, all DMs are immune to Mines, Fighters "
"(their weaponry is too small to affect them), and Cloaking (they are "
"equipped with the highest level of Scanners)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:357
msgid ""
"• The player does not get the Fleet Size Bonus (MRB 5.1.3) for "
"outnumbering a DM."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:358
msgid ""
"• A roll of 1 is not an automatic hit on a DM. However, a roll of 1 by a "
"DM is always a hit. A DM that rolls a 10 is always a miss."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:359
msgid ""
"• DMs carry damage from combat to combat (they do not automatically "
"heal). However, they do heal two damage instantly every time they destroy"
" a planet (whether or not it has a Colony)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:360
msgid ""
"• DMs get more than one attack per round as shown on the table (2.5). All"
" attacks are of the same strength and occur at the same time. A DM is "
"considered to have Tactics 2."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:361
msgid ""
"• The player should use common sense when allocating the attacks of a DM."
" If weak against Fighters, it should target Fighters. If weak against "
"large fleets, it should attack smaller ships or damaged ships in order to"
" get the fleet size under 10, etc. Like with human players, DMs may roll "
"their attacks one at a time and see the result before rolling more "
"attacks."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:362
msgid "• A DM never retreats from combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:368 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2893
msgid "Doomsday Machine Strength"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:370 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2895
msgid "DM Rating Defense Strength Attack Strength Hull Size Number of Attacks"
msgstr ""

