#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:510
msgid "Doomsday Machines – Hidden GC"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:512
msgid ""
"• Features: The GC represents an ancient, super-advanced civilization. "
"You may not attack a GC but combat with the DM may occur in the GC hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:513
msgid ""
"• GC Discovery: The GC’s location is not known at the start of the game. "
"The GC counter is seeded into an assortment of Deep Space markers "
"randomly placed near you."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:514
msgid ""
"The GC will randomly appear along the edge of your Home System markers. "
"Set aside the GC counter when assembling the random Deep Space counters "
"for a scenario. Also set aside 9 random Deep Space counters. The GC is "
"added face down, at random to the separated Deep Space counters. Place "
"these separate DS counters adjacent to your HS in hexes indicated by the "
"blue dots. The DM does not cause these DS markers to be flipped, see "
"2.3.6."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:515
msgid ""
"• GC Trade: You may trade with the GC by extending your MS Pipelines to "
"the GC hex as if it were one of your colonies. Instead of gaining 1 CP "
"for this colony, you receive 5 CP per Econ Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:516
msgid ""
"• GC Loss Condition: If the GC is eliminated, you lose just as if your "
"own HW had been captured or eliminated."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:522
msgid "Space Amoebas"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:524
msgid ""
"During the game, the Space Amoebas will multiply and attempt to destroy "
"the human player. There are similar rules for Space Amoebas included in "
"the Competitive Scenario Book (CSB 10.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:533
msgid ""
"• Take ten of the 10 CP Deep Space Mineral markers and four of the Deep "
"Space Barren Planets and mix them up. Place them in the 14 Deep Space "
"hexes labeled “DS.” Do not use any other Deep Space markers. Leave the "
"other Deep Space hexes empty."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:534
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 7"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:535
msgid ""
"• There are three types of Giant Space Amoebas included in the game. One "
"is placed in each hex marked with an “A.”"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:543
msgid ""
"• The following rules are not used: Minesweepers, Non-Player Aliens, "
"Boarding Ships, Ground Combat, Titans, Facilities, and Ship Experience."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:544
msgid "• The player pays no maintenance during this game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:545
msgid "• The Barren Planets do not have Non-Player Aliens on them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:546
msgid ""
"• As in the multiplayer Space Amoeba scenarios, Minesweepers (SW) "
"represent Science Vessels (SV), which are needed to defeat the Amoebas. "
"Science (aka Minesweeper) technology much be researched to produce "
"Science Vessels. Use the costs for Minesweeper ships and Minesweeper "
"technology for producing Science Vessels."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:547
msgid ""
"• Researching Minesweepers (SW) instead gets the player Science Vessels "
"(SV) which are needed to defeat the Amoebas. Actual Minesweepers are not "
"used in this scenario."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:548
msgid ""
"• There are only two levels of Science technology. Ignore Minesweeper 3 "
"technology for this scenario."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:549 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:552
msgid ""
"Design Note: Yes, I know it says SW on the counters, but in this "
"scenario, it is also as if they say SV, as in Science Vessels. Pretend "
"that the SW was put on the counter by someone who heard the words "
"“Science Vessel” spoken by someone with a bad TV Russian accent (I’m "
"looking at you, Chekov)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:560
msgid "The human player wins by destroying"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:561
msgid "all Space Amoebas."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:567
msgid "Researching Space Amoebas"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:569
msgid ""
"•Science technology cannot be researched by the player until at least one"
" ship has been lost to any Amoeba. The player may move a “brave” ship "
"into an Amoeba’s hex in order to find out what is coming toward their "
"empire. Note to self: Don’t ever be a Scout pilot."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:570
msgid ""
"• Until the player has researched each Amoeba, on a type-by-type basis, "
"they cannot be attacked and will destroy all the player’s"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:571
msgid ""
"ships (except SVs) in the same hex. If SVs are present, they may research"
" the Amoeba before it destroys the other ships. If those SVs gather 10 or"
" more Research Points on that Amoeba type, the other ships will not be "
"automatically destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:572
msgid ""
"• Research Points carry over from turn to turn. A separate note should be"
" kept on each type of Space Amoeba."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:573
msgid ""
"• Each turn an SV is in the same hex with an Amoeba, one or more dice are"
" rolled for each SV to represent that ship’s research into that type of "
"Amoeba."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:574
msgid "- 1-2: Two Research Points gained."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:575
msgid "- 3-5: One Research Point gained."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:576
msgid "- 6-8: Nothing."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:577
msgid "- 9-10: SV destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:578
msgid "• Level 1 Science Vessels roll one die when researching."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:579
msgid "• Level 2 Science Vessels get to roll two dice and take the best result."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:580
msgid ""
"• Level 2 Science technology can’t be researched until a Level 1 SV has "
"made at least one research attempt on any one type of Amoeba."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:581
msgid ""
"• Each individual Amoeba does not need to be researched, but each TYPE "
"must be. Once the player has a total of 10 Research Points on a certain "
"TYPE of Amoeba, they may attack any Amoeba of that type for the rest of "
"the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:582
msgid ""
"• A Science Vessel may research an Amoeba on the same turn the ship moves"
" into its hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:583
msgid "• Multiple SVs can research each turn they are in a hex with an Amoeba."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:584
msgid ""
"• If an SV shares a hex with an Amoeba type that has been completely "
"researched, that ship does not participate in the combat but must still "
"roll a die for research as normal and may be destroyed on a roll of 9-10."
" No further Research Points are gained."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:585
msgid ""
"• After 10 Research Points have been gathered on a type of Amoeba, those "
"Amoebas will no longer automatically destroy ships. Instead, combat "
"ensues as normal. However, Science Vessels never participate in combat "
"with an Amoeba."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:591
msgid "Space Amoeba Characteristics"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:593 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:599
msgid ""
"Design Note: In sci-fi terms, the Amoeba can be killed if the player "
"slightly tweaks their weapons – by adjusting the frequency to the upper "
"EM band, by adjusting the phase, by reversing the polarity, or by doing "
"something else pseudo-scientific sounding. The specific adjustment is not"
" important. It means it is now possible to (immediately) attack them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:594
msgid ""
"After 10 Research Points have been gathered on a type of Amoeba, the "
"Amoeba’s characteristics are determined. Roll on the Amoeba "
"Characteristics Table and flip all Amoebas of that type to the "
"“researched” side. No two (or more) types of Amoebas will have the same "
"characteristics. Reroll any repeat result."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:595
msgid ""
"No retrofit (technology upgrade) is needed for ships in order to attack "
"(MRB 9.11.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:596
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 8"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:605
msgid "Amoeba Characteristics Table"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:607
msgid "Roll Characteristics"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:608 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:619
msgid "C7-1-1"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:609
msgid "D6-2-2"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:610 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:620
msgid "A7-2-2. This type of Amoeba is also vulnerable to fighters."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:611
msgid "A7-2-2. This type of Amoeba becomes an A5-1-2 when faced by ONLY Raiders."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:612 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:621
msgid ""
"B5-1-2. These Amoebas have voracious appetites and get two attacks each "
"round. Each of these attacks may lead to a Chain Attack (3.6.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:613
msgid ""
"A7-2-2. In any round in which there are 3 or more different types of "
"ships (for example: SC, DD, and CA) attacking these Amoebas, all "
"attacking ships get +1 to their attack."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:614
msgid "6-7"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:615 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:622
msgid ""
"These Amoebas can only be killed by detonating a ship inside them, no "
"adjustment to weapons will work on this type of Amoeba. Only one ship may"
" attempt this per turn. If the ship is a CA, BC, BB, or DN, the Amoeba is"
" destroyed. If the ship is a DD or MB the Amoeba is destroyed on a roll "
"of 1-8 and if the ship is a SC the Amoeba is destroyed on a roll of 1-4. "
"In all cases, the ship attempting this is destroyed. Only the ships "
"listed here can be used. If the Amoeba survives, other ships in the hex "
"with the Amoeba are destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:616 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:623
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1075 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1085
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4719 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4723
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4792 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4796
msgid "8-10"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:629
msgid "Amoeba Properties"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:631
msgid "• All Amoebas have a Tactics level of 2."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:632
msgid ""
"• All Amoebas are immune to Cloaking and Fighters unless otherwise "
"specified."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:633
msgid "• Ships never get a Fleet Size Bonus (MRB 5.1.3) against Amoebas."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:639
msgid "Amoeba Target Priority"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:641
msgid "Each time an Amoeba attacks,"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:642
msgid ""
"these mindless denizens of the interstellar void roll a die to determine "
"which ship they will attempt to swallow (attack). On a roll of 1-5 it "
"will attack the smallest ship in combat. On a roll of 6-10 it will attack"
" the largest ship in the combat. Use the CP value of a ship to determine "
"largest and smallest. Since Flagships are irreplaceable, they are "
"considered to have the highest CP value. If there is a tie, the player "
"chooses the target of the Space Amoeba. If a player chooses to, they may "
"allow their SVs to be attacked."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:648
msgid "Amoeba Attack Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:650
msgid "The Amoeba rolls one die"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:651
msgid ""
"and executes the attack normally, comparing its Attack Strength to the "
"ship’s Defense Strength (including technology). However, larger ships are"
" even harder to swallow. Ships with a Hull Size of 2 get an extra +1 to "
"their Defense Strength and ships with a Hull Size of 3 (or larger) get an"
" extra +2 to their Defense Strength. A successful attack results in the "
"ship being swallowed (destroyed) regardless of size. As always, a roll of"
" a 1 is a successful attack and will swallow a ship, regardless of size."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:657
msgid "Chain Attacks"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:659
msgid "If an Amoeba successfully swallows"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:660
msgid ""
"a ship, and rolls 2 or less than was needed, then the extra energy gained"
" from swallowing the ship allows the Amoeba to immediately attack again. "
"This can happen any number of times during a round of combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:661
msgid ""
"EXAMPLE: A Type 4 Amoeba (A7-2-2) is being attacked by four Scouts, a "
"Cruiser, and a Battleship. All of the ships have Defense technology 1. "
"The Amoeba attacks first. It rolls a 3 and so will attack the smallest "
"ship (a Scout). On its attack, it rolls a 4. Since it needed a 6, the "
"Amoeba not only swallows the Scout but gets to attack again. This time it"
" rolls a 6 and will attack the largest ship (the Battleship). The "
"Battleship has a Defense Strength of 5 (Defense of 2 + Defense Tech 1 + 2"
" because of Hull Size 3). The Amoeba rolls a 1, swallowing the "
"Battleship. However, since it was only one less than was needed, it does "
"not get to make a further chain attack."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:667
msgid "Amoeba Healing"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:669
msgid "After combat, damage to an Amoeba"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:670
msgid "is healed in the same way as ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:676
msgid "Spreading of Space Amoebas"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:678
msgid ""
"Amoebas never move. Once placed, an Amoeba counter never moves to a new "
"hex. Instead, Amoebas spread. At the start of an Economic Phase (before "
"the player makes any purchases), each Amoeba that is adjacent to a hex "
"without an Amoeba may spread. Place a new Amoeba of the same type in the "
"adjacent hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:684
msgid "Spread Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:686
msgid "The following guidelines and"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:687
msgid "restrictions apply to the spreading:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:688
msgid ""
"• Space Amoebas begin to spread during the Economic Phase indicated on "
"the Difficulty Table (3.9)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:689
msgid "• Only one Amoeba may ever be in a hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:690
msgid ""
"• Spreading is automatic; however, each Amoeba may only spread one time "
"into one hex during an Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:691
msgid ""
"• If more than one type of Amoeba is adjacent to an open hex, the human "
"player may decide which Amoeba spreads into the hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:692
msgid ""
"• If an Amoeba may spread into more than one hex, the player chooses "
"which hex it spreads into. However, the player must choose in such a way "
"to allow for maximum Amoeba spreading. If another open hex is available, "
"they cannot have an Amoeba spread into a hex that would stop a different "
"Amoeba from spreading."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:693
msgid ""
"• Unlike in multiplayer Amoeba scenarios, the spreading of Amoebas is not"
" affected by the presence or absence of planets."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:694
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 9"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:695
msgid ""
"• Newly placed Amoebas do not spread. New Amoebas placed that Economic "
"Phase should be marked in some way so that they are not accidentally "
"selected to spread."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:696
msgid ""
"• Because Amoebas are attracted to the energy signature of the player’s "
"Empires, they will never spread outside of the map area denoted by the "
"chosen scenario map."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:697
msgid ""
"• Amoebas are not limited by the counter mix or quantity. If you run out "
"of one type, use a counter of another type and place a numeral marker on "
"it to show the true type of the Amoeba. Use substitutions when necessary."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:703
msgid "Amoeba Contact with Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:705
msgid "If there are ships in the hex"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:706
msgid ""
"in which an Amoeba spreads, a special combat round occurs immediately "
"during the Economic Phase, with the Amoeba as the attacker. Of course, if"
" that type of Amoeba has not been fully researched yet, it automatically "
"destroys all ships that are not Science Vessels."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:712
msgid "Amoeba Contact with System Markers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:714
msgid "An Amoeba"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:715
msgid ""
"removes the System marker (whether explored or not) in any hex in which "
"it spreads (only after defeating any ships present). If a hex has not "
"been explored, the Amoeba spreads normally and the System marker is "
"removed, sight unseen."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:716
msgid ""
"If a Black Hole has been revealed, an Amoeba will not spread into that "
"hex. In all other cases, Amoebas are unaffected by System markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:722
msgid "Space Amoebas and Mines"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:724
msgid ""
"Space Amoebas are hindered from spreading by Mines. However, Mines never "
"affect Amoebas like they do ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:730
msgid "Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:732
msgid "If the player moves only a Mine (or a Mine"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:733
msgid ""
"and a Science Vessel) into the same hex as an Amoeba, no combat occurs. "
"In the Economic Phase, the Mine is removed, and that Amoeba does not "
"spread during that one Economic Phase. No other harm comes to the Amoeba."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:739
msgid "Contact with Mines"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:741
msgid "Amoebas may spread onto Mines"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:742
msgid ""
"normally; in which case the Mines have no effect and are removed from the"
" map. A Mine only stops an Amoeba from spreading if it is in the same hex"
" as the Amoeba at the start of the Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:748
msgid "Adapting to Mines"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:750
msgid "See CSB 10.8.3. However,"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:751
msgid "when an Amoeba adapts to Mines, it only affects Amoebas of that type."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:757
msgid "One Roll per Economic Phase"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:759
msgid "The roll to see if the"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:760
msgid ""
"Amoebas adapt to Mines is made only once per Amoeba type per Economic "
"Phase, regardless of how many Amoebas were prevented from spreading."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:766
msgid "Difficulty Table"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:768
msgid ""
"Space Amoebas do NOT spread in the first Economic Phase. The difficulty "
"level of the game is determined by the Economic Phase in which the "
"Amoebas start to spread."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:769
msgid "Difficulty Amoebas start spreading in Economic Phase"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:775 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:782
msgid "4*"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:776
msgid "* Both the Attack and Defense Strength of all Amoebas are increased by 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:788
msgid "Solitaire Alien Empire - Non-"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:790 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1188
msgid "Victory Point Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:798
msgid "One player sets up and plays their"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:799
msgid ""
"empire as normal. Two or three Alien Players (APs) are trying to destroy "
"the human player. The player wins by destroying the Homeworlds of all "
"APs. The game can continue beyond Econ Phase 20. If it does, alternate "
"the rolls on the AP Economic Sheet between rows 19 and 20."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:807
msgid "The human player may not use Decoys."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:808
msgid ""
"There is no need for a turn order bid – the human player always takes "
"their turn before the APs and the APs always resolve their Economic "
"Phases after the player. Barren Planets found in Deep Space are not "
"inhabited by Non-Player Aliens (NPAs; MRB 18.0). In general, where the "
"solitaire rules are silent, use common sense and play the APs "
"intelligently."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:809
msgid "Only Basic Units Types are used (MRB 8)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:810
msgid "Fast Technology is not used (MRB 9.9)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:811
msgid "Empire Advantages are not used (MRB 10)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:812
msgid "Alien Technology cards are not used (MRB 11)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:813
msgid "Crew Cards are not used (MRB 12)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:814
msgid "Defense Satellite Networks are not used (MRB 14)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:815
msgid "Additional Terrain (MRB 25) may be used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:816
msgid "Doomsday Machines (MRB 29) may be used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:817
msgid "Instant Technology Upgrades (MRB 30) may be used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:818
msgid "Black Hole Slingshots (MRB 31) may be used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:819
msgid "All other rules after MRB 18 are not used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:820
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 10"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:826
msgid "Alien Player Homeworlds"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:828
msgid ""
"• APs each have a Homeworld. Use the Homeworlds and ships from the unused"
" player colors. An AP Homeworld represents the entire empire and "
"resources of that AP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:829
msgid "• Each AP starts with one Base on their Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:830
msgid ""
"• APs never use MS Pipelines, Colony Ships, Shipyards, Mining Ships, or "
"Decoys."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:831
msgid ""
"• An AP is eliminated when its Homeworld is eliminated. At that point it "
"will no longer produce ships, but existing ships will continue to fight "
"to the death (unlike human players that are eliminated in multiplayer "
"games)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:832
msgid ""
"• Until an AP launches a fleet (4.3), the only actions that need to be "
"taken for them (other than defending against an attack) occur in the "
"Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:833
msgid "• In combat, the AP never screens ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:839
msgid "AP Economic Rolls"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:841
msgid ""
"During the Economic Phase, after the player completes their actions, each"
" AP takes the following actions:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:842
msgid ""
"• APs make their Economic Roll(s). As seen on the “Alien Economic Sheet” "
"found on page 56, each AP starts with one Economic Roll (Econ Roll). Each"
" of these rolls is made on the appropriate table for the Economic Phase. "
"If the result of the roll is Economy, then an Extra Economic Roll (Extra "
"Econ) will be gained every Economic Phase starting three Economic Phases "
"after that result. That is why 0 is written in the Extra Econ column for "
"the first three Economic Phases. For example, if Economy is rolled on "
"turn 1, then an Extra Economic Roll will be gained starting on the fourth"
" Economic Phase. These extra rolls persist for the rest of the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:843 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:854
msgid ""
"• If any other result is rolled, a number of CP (5, 10, or 15) is added "
"in the appropriate column for that turn depending on the difficulty level"
" (see below). CP put in the Defense column are doubled. These columns "
"(Fleet, Technology, Defense) represent what the AP has “in the bank” in "
"each area. These totals carry over from turn to turn and accumulate until"
" an AP spends them. When an AP spends in one of these areas, it always "
"spends all the available resources in that area that it can. The Defense "
"column maxes out at 50 CP, excess is placed into Fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:844
msgid "• One die is rolled for each of the Economic Rolls that the AP has."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:845
msgid "Difficulty # of AP # of CP per roll"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:850 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:857
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3467 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3485
msgid "Really Tough"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:863
msgid "AP Fleet Launch Rolls"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:865 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:873
msgid ""
"When all Economic Rolls have been made, the Fleet Launch roll is made. "
"One die is rolled. The result necessary for Fleet Launch is indicated on "
"the “Alien Economic Sheet” and changes each Economic Phase. If the Fleet "
"Launch die roll is unsuccessful, the AP is done for the Economic Phase. A"
" fleet will never launch if there is less than 6 CP in the Fleet column "
"or if there are already 3 fleets in play for this AP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:866
msgid ""
"• If the AP has researched Fighter Tech and has at least 27 CP in the "
"Fleet column and the human player has not shown a level of Point Defense "
"Tech equivalent to the AP’s own Fighter Tech, apply a -2 modifier to the "
"Fleet Launch roll."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:867
msgid ""
"• If the AP has researched Cloaking Tech and has at least 12 CP in the "
"Fleet column and the human player has not shown a level of Scanner Tech "
"equivalent to the AP’s own Cloaking Tech, apply a -2 modifier to the "
"Fleet Launch roll. This is cumulative with the DRM from the bullet above"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:868
msgid ""
"• If a Fleet Launch is made, then the AP will determine whether the fleet"
" is a Raider fleet (4.4). If it is a Raider fleet, then the entire fleet "
"is built at that time."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:869
msgid ""
"• If it is not a Raider fleet, then the fleet is not built until it "
"enters combat for the first time. Use any ship counter to represent an AP"
" non-Raider fleet. Subtract all the CP from the Fleet column and write "
"the CP in the ledger on the right side of the “Alien Economic Sheet”. "
"When it is time to build this AP fleet, use this CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:870
msgid "• All new fleets are placed on this AP’s Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:879
msgid "AP Raider Fleets"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:881
msgid "A fleet will be a Raider fleet if the conditions below are met:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:882
msgid "• The AP has already researched Cloaking technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:883
msgid "• The AP has at least 12 CP in the Fleet column."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:884
msgid ""
"• The AP has not seen a level of Scanner technology equivalent to the "
"AP’s own Cloaking technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:885
msgid ""
"Whenever an AP launches a Raider fleet, the AP builds nothing but Raiders"
" for that fleet. A Raider fleet has different movement priorities as "
"indicated in section 4.7.2."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:886
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 11"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:892
msgid "AP Technology Purchasing"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:894 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:901
msgid "• Alien Players automatically start with Mine technology (MRB 17.1)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:895 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:902
msgid ""
"• The AP does not attempt to purchase technology if less than 20 CP are "
"in the Tech Column, including Movement technology (see next bullet)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:896
msgid ""
"• Whenever a fleet is launched, roll for Movement technology. On a roll "
"of 1-4, the AP will purchase the next Movement technology available if it"
" has enough CP in the Tech column. Subtract the appropriate number of CP "
"and note that tech as purchased."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:897
msgid "• Technologies other than Movement are not purchased until combat occurs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:898
msgid ""
"• When the fleet is engaged in combat for the first time, the AP will "
"spend all available tech CP purchasing technology and then will build the"
" fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:908
msgid "Order of Purchases"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:910
msgid "Techs cost are the same as for the"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:911
msgid ""
"player. Revealed player technology is known by/shared among all AP teams."
" Once engaged in combat, all available tech CP will be spent in the "
"following order. If the AP already has the listed tech, skip the bullet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:912
msgid ""
"• If this is a Raider fleet with Cloaking 1, roll a die. On a roll of "
"1-6, the AP will buy Cloaking 2 if it has the tech CP to make the "
"purchase. On a roll of 7-10 the AP will proceed to the chart below."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:913
msgid ""
"• If the human player has used Fighters in combat and the AP does not "
"have Point Defense Tech, it will purchase Point Defense 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:914
msgid ""
"• Next, if the human player has shown Mines, and the AP does not have "
"Minesweeper Tech, it will purchase Minesweeper 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:915
msgid ""
"• Next, if the human player has used Raiders in combat, and the AP does "
"not have a Scanner technology level capable of detecting those Raiders, "
"roll a die. On a roll of 1-4, the AP will purchase a level of Scanner "
"Tech able to detect the Raiders. If the AP would need to purchase two "
"levels of Scanning Tech but can only afford one, it will purchase one "
"level in an effort to work toward that goal. On a roll of 5-10, the AP "
"will not purchase Scanners during this combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:916
msgid ""
"• Next the AP will determine if it spends tech CP on Ship Size "
"technology. This depends on its current Ship Size level. Only roll once "
"on the Ship Size Table below regardless of how many tech CP the AP has to"
" spend."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:917 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:943
msgid "1 2 3 4 5"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:918
msgid "Current Ship Size:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:919 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:944
msgid "Roll needed to Purchase next level: Auto 1-7 1-6 1-5 1-3"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:920
msgid ""
"• If the AP has researched Fighter technology and the human player has "
"not shown Point Defense, roll a die. On a roll of 1-6, the AP will buy "
"the next level of Fighter technology. On a roll of 7-10, the AP will "
"proceed to the chart below."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:921
msgid ""
"• If there are tech CP remaining, then the AP will roll on the Technology"
" Purchase Table below to determine which technology is purchased. If a "
"technology is rolled that is too expensive, reroll until a tech is rolled"
" that can be afforded or stop rolling if no more technology can be "
"afforded."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:922
msgid ""
"AP ships are always at the current level of all their researched "
"technologies; they instantly upgrade when a new technology is purchased."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:923
msgid "Die Roll Technology Purchased"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:925 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:946
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4944
msgid "Attack"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:927 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4945
msgid "Defense"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:928 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:947
msgid "5*"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:929 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:948
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4950
msgid "Tactics"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:930
msgid "6**"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:931
msgid "Cloak"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:932 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:949
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4947
msgid "Scan"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:933 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4946
msgid "Fighter"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:934 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:950
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3887 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3905
msgid "Point Defense"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:935
msgid "Minesweeper"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:936
msgid ""
"*If Tactics are rolled and the AP is not yet at Attack 2 or Defense 2, "
"then it will purchase the lower of Attack or Defense (randomly if tied) "
"instead of Tactics."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:937
msgid "**If the human player has shown Scanner 2 in combat, reroll any 6s."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:938
msgid ""
"• If at any point in the above process the AP does not have enough tech "
"CP available to make the purchase, then the purchase is not made. Proceed"
" to the next bullet in the list."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:939
msgid ""
"• The AP will only buy one level of any counter technology (e.g. Scanner)"
" in advance, rerolling such results, unless they have seen the matching "
"technology in play."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:940
msgid ""
"• Finally, when the AP does not have enough tech CP available to purchase"
" a technology, then no more tech is purchased, and the remaining points "
"are recorded in the Tech column."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:956
msgid "AP Fleet Building"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:958
msgid ""
"After all tech CP have been spent, all available fleet CP are used to "
"purchase ships in the following order."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:959
msgid "• If this is a Raider fleet, all of the points are spent on Raiders."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:960
msgid ""
"• If the AP has Fighter technology and the human player has not shown "
"Point Defense in combat, the AP will create a Carrier fleet by spending "
"all available points on Carriers and Fighters to max out the number of "
"full Carriers in the fleet (Carrier and three Fighters) before spending "
"the rest of the CP according to 4.6.1. If it does not have enough for a "
"full Carrier, it will not purchase Fighters or Carriers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:961
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 12"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:962
msgid ""
"• If the AP has Fighter technology and the human player has shown Point "
"Defense in combat, roll a die. The AP will only build a Carrier fleet as "
"indicated above on a roll of 1-4. On a roll of 5-10, if a fleet with a "
"value of 12 CP or more is launched and the AP has a level of Cloaking "
"technology for which the human player has not shown a level of Scanner "
"technology that could detect it then the fleet being built is a Raider "
"fleet. Otherwise, proceed to 4.6.1 below."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:968
msgid "Building Priorities"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:970
msgid "If not a Raider fleet, then the AP will"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:971
msgid ""
"purchase ships in the following order. • LARGEST SHIP FIRST: The first "
"ship built will be the largest ship that the AP’s Ship Size technology "
"and fleet CP will allow it to buy."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:972
msgid ""
"• POSSIBLE DESTROYER: If the AP has researched a level of Scanner "
"technology that is equal to or superior to the level of Cloaking that the"
" human player has shown in combat – and the first ship it built (the "
"largest) was not a Destroyer – the AP will next build one Destroyer if "
"its technology level and CP allow."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:973
msgid ""
"• REMAINING SHIPS: Next, roll the die and consult the Fleet Composition "
"table below to determine the composition of the rest of the fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:974
msgid "Die Roll Fleet Composition"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:975 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:983
msgid "3 or less"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:976 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:984
msgid "Largest Fleet"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:977
msgid "4-6 Balanced"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:978 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:985
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4711 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4715
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4784 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4788
msgid "7-10"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:979 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:986
msgid "Largest Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:980
msgid ""
"• DIE ROLL MODIFIER: If the human player has used Fighters in combat "
"previously in this game, and the AP has Point Defense technology, apply a"
" -2 modifier to the roll on the above table. If the modified result is "
"4-10 – and the AP fleet does not contain at least one Carrier with three "
"Fighters – the AP will first spend 12 CP to build two Scouts before "
"building the rest of the fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:992
msgid "Remaining Fleet Composition"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:994
msgid "The following is"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:995
msgid ""
"an explanation of the possible results found on the Fleet Composition "
"table above."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:996
msgid ""
"• LARGEST FLEET: The remaining points will be spent on purchasing as many"
" ships as possible. Ships larger than a Scout will only be purchased if "
"it would not lower fleet size. For instance, 17 CP would result in the "
"purchase of a Scout and a Destroyer, but 18 CP would result in the "
"purchase of three Scouts (not two Destroyers)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:997
msgid ""
"• LARGEST SHIPS: The remaining points will be spent on purchasing the "
"largest ships possible. For instance, if there was an AP with a Ship Size"
" Tech of 2, 18 CP would result in the purchase of 2 DDs, while 17 CP "
"would result in the purchase of one Destroyer and one Scout."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:998
msgid ""
"• BALANCED: The remaining points will be spent on purchasing as many "
"ships as possible that can use the highest"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:999
msgid ""
"Attack and Defense technology that the AP has. Extra points would be used"
" to build larger ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1000
msgid ""
"EXAMPLE: The AP has technology that allows it to build Battleships but "
"only has Attack 3 and Defense 1. If it had 24 CP available, it would "
"build two Cruisers to take advantage of having Attack 2. If it had 27 CP,"
" it would build one Cruiser and one Battlecruiser. If it had 30 CP, it "
"would build two Battlecruisers. If it had 32 CP, it would build one "
"Cruiser and one Battleship. If it had 36 CP, it would build 3 Cruisers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1001
msgid "• Ship purchase is always limited by the AP’s Ship Size technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1002
msgid ""
"• If there are CP left over from a fleet such that another ship cannot be"
" built, credit the remainder back to the Fleet column."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1008
msgid "No Minesweepers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1010
msgid "If the AP has Minesweeper"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1011
msgid ""
"technology, all their Scouts are automatically equipped with this "
"technology. An AP never purchases Minesweeper ships; the technology is "
"carried on their Scouts."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1017
msgid "AP Fleet Movement"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1024 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1696
msgid "Non-Raider Fleet Movement"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1026
msgid "AP fleets move differently"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1027
msgid ""
"than Doomsday Machines (2.1). They evaluate the following Movement "
"priorities at the start of every Move."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1028
msgid ""
"• An AP fleet will always move toward the Colony it can reach in the "
"fewest number of Economic Phases, keeping in mind the three movement "
"turns between each Economic Phase. For example, on the first turn after "
"an Economic Phase, an AP fleet with a Movement technology level 1 will "
"equally consider a colony 2 hexes away and another colony 3 hexes away "
"among its priorities (see below) since it can reach both before the next "
"Econ Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1029 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1041
msgid ""
"• If more than one Colony qualifies, an AP fleet will move toward the "
"Colony that is undefended. When determining this, a Colony with Shipyards"
" and a single SC is not considered to be defended (the AP has a spy "
"network and knows this)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1030
msgid ""
"• If there is more than one undefended Colony that it can reach in the "
"same number of Economic Phases, then it will move toward the Colony that "
"it can reach in the fewest number of moves."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1031
msgid ""
"• If there are no undefended Colonies but multiple defended Colonies that"
" it can reach in the same number of Economic Phases, then it will move "
"toward the Colony that it can reach in the fewest number of moves. If "
"still tied, it will move toward the Colony that is largest. If still "
"tied, it will move toward the Colony that brings it closer to the "
"player’s Homeworld. If still tied, the player chooses."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1032 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1042
msgid ""
"• Once a non-raider AP fleet reaches a Colony, it will stay there until "
"the Colony is destroyed. AP fleets never retreat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1033 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1043
msgid ""
"• An AP fleet will not enter hexes with Supernovas, Cosmic Storms, or "
"Black Holes."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1034
msgid ""
"• Asteroids and Nebulae do not affect their movement (they still affect "
"combat; MRB 5.8). Because of this, An AP will sometimes have a choice on "
"whether to stop in open space, in Asteroids, or in Nebulae. Whenever this"
" choice must be made, the AP will always stop in the hex that benefits "
"them"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1035
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 13"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1036 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1044
msgid ""
"the most in combat when comparing the known technologies of the AP and "
"the human player. However, an AP will never move less than its full "
"movement to stop in such a hex. The AP treats Quasars in a similar manner"
" to Asteroids/Nebulae. The AP moves through Folds in Space as would a "
"player’s ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1037
msgid ""
"• If an AP moves into a hex with an unexplored marker, it does not flip "
"the marker. A player may not move into a hex with an AP fleet and an "
"unexplored System marker. If you wanted to move there you should have "
"explored it before the AP reached that hex! The hex can still be explored"
" by Exploration technology (MRB 9.8)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1038
msgid ""
"• If an AP fleet can attack a single revealed ship without delaying it "
"reaching its destination, it will. It will avoid combat with non-single "
"ships (going around them) as long as doing so would not delay it from "
"reaching its destination."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1050 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4916
msgid "Raider Fleet Movement"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1052
msgid "Raider fleets move the same as"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1053
msgid ""
"normal fleets, except that they will avoid combat (if possible) with "
"human player fleets unless the Raider fleet is larger than them in terms "
"of CP. This is true even at Colonies."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1054
msgid ""
"• Whereas a non-Raider fleet will sometimes attack strongly guarded "
"Colonies (because the nearest unguarded Colony is not within range in the"
" same number of Economic Phases), a Raider fleet will never do that. They"
" will only attack a Colony if they have a larger fleet than is guarding "
"it. If not, they will move towards a different Colony. Even if the "
"player’s ships are unrevealed, the player should tally up the size of "
"their fleets to make this determination."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1055
msgid ""
"EXAMPLE: A Raider fleet of two Raiders (24 CP) can reach three different "
"Colonies in the same number of Econ Phases. One Colony is guarded by 4 "
"SCs (24 CP). The Raider fleet is not stronger and will therefore not "
"attack that fleet, avoiding that Colony. The next Colony is guarded by 3 "
"SCs (18 CP), but near the Colony is a fleet of 3 DDs (27 CP). The last "
"Colony is guarded by 1 BB (20 CP). Since the two Colonies are both "
"guarded by a fleet that is smaller than the Raider fleet (in CP value), "
"the Raider fleet will move toward the Colony that is closest; the "
"proximity of the Destroyer fleet did not affect the Raider fleet’s choice"
" of Colony. If there had been a fourth Colony that could be reached in "
"the same number of Economic Phases and that one had only a SY present, "
"the Raider fleet would move toward that Colony because it is considered "
"unguarded."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1056
msgid ""
"• If a Colony that a Raider fleet was moving towards suddenly becomes "
"guarded by a force that is equal to it in terms of points, that Raider "
"fleet will move toward the next closest Colony at that point. If "
"necessary, it would even move through or past an enemy fleet to attack a "
"Colony or ship behind it."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1062
msgid "AP Homeworld Defense (Defense CP)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1064
msgid ""
"Defense CP are not used until an AP Homeworld is attacked. When the "
"attack takes place (before the dice are rolled), the AP will spend all "
"the points available in the Fleet, Tech, and Defense columns of the "
"“Alien Economic Sheet” to build fleets, Bases, and Mines to be used "
"defending their Homeworld. It will do this following the same procedure "
"as if it were a fleet (launch, buy tech, build fleet), except that it "
"will not roll for the possibility of purchasing Movement"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1065
msgid ""
"technology (4.5) and it will reroll any 10s on the Technology Purchase "
"Table (4.5.1)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1066
msgid ""
"• Remember that APs start with Mine technology and that points should "
"have been doubled when originally added to the Defense column."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1067
msgid ""
"• The AP will defend its Homeworld using the Base it started with (if it "
"has not been destroyed) in addition to spending all CP in both the "
"Defense and Fleet columns."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1068
msgid ""
"• CP in the Fleet column are spent exactly as if a fleet was being "
"constructed, except that this fleet will not be a Raider fleet. These "
"ships will aid in the defense of the Homeworld. If any AP ships survive "
"until the AP’s next turn, they will immediately launch as a fleet, "
"following all normal launch procedures."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1069
msgid ""
"• There is no effect to an AP Homeworld being blockaded. If a player’s "
"ships are in that hex during the Economic Phase, the AP will execute its "
"Economic Phase normtally, including automatically launching a fleet, "
"building mines, and building bases (see below). Any combats that might "
"occur due to this are resolved during the first Turn unless the player’s "
"ships move away first."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1070
msgid ""
"• CP in the Defense column are spent on either Bases or Mines. Aliens may"
" have more than one Base at their Homeworld. Roll a die and consult the "
"table below."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1071
msgid "Roll Defense Composition"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1072 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1083
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4821 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4827
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4828 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4829
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4831 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4833
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4835 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4844
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4850 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4851
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4852 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4854
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4856 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4858
msgid "1-3"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1073 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1084
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3956
msgid "Mines"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1074
msgid "4-7 Balanced"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1076 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1086
msgid "Most Bases"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1077
msgid "• MINES: All available defense CP will be spent on mines."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1078
msgid ""
"• BALANCED: The AP will build a Base first, followed by a Mine, and then "
"continue alternating purchases. The rest being spent on Mines once there "
"are not enough CP left to purchase a Base."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1079
msgid ""
"• MOST BASES: All available defense CP will be spent on Bases, with the "
"rest being spent on Mines once there are not enough CP left to purchase a"
" Base."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1080
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 14"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1092
msgid "Alien Player Map #1"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1094
msgid ""
"• There are 26 Home System markers for the player. The Homeworld is "
"placed in the hex with an “H.”"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1095
msgid "• Deep Space markers are placed as per the map above."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1096 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1116
msgid ""
"• If there are two Alien empires, the Alien Homeworlds are placed on the "
"“2s.”"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1097 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1117
msgid ""
"• If there are three Alien empires, the Alien Homeworlds are placed on "
"the “2s” and the “3.”"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1098 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1119
msgid "• The player should use the 20 CP Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1099
msgid ""
"• The AP Difficulty Level chart (4.2) determines the number of APs and "
"the number of CP per roll."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1105
msgid "Alien Player Map #2"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1107 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1191
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1205
msgid "X"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1108 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1109
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1194 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1208
msgid "Player 1 Home System Markers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1110 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1111
msgid "D e e p S p a c e"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1112 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1113
msgid "S ys t e m M a r k e r s"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1114
msgid "2 2"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1115
msgid ""
"• Only 25 Home System markers are used for the player. Remove the Black "
"Hole from the Home System markers. The Homeworld is placed in the hex "
"with an “X”. Deep Space markers are placed within 7 hexes of the player’s"
" Home System, except on hexes with the 2s and the 3."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1118
msgid ""
"• If an AP that started in one of the “2” positions (on the edge of the "
"map) has a choice between two Colonies to attack and the defenses are the"
" same, it will attack the Colony that is closest to its side of the "
"board."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1120
msgid ""
"• The AP Difficulty Level chart (4.2) determines the number of Alien "
"Players and the number of CP per roll."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1126
msgid "Using Close Encounters"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1128
msgid "Rules in Solitaire Alien Empire Scenarios - Non- Victory Point Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1129
msgid ""
"It is possible to play Solitaire Scenarios (4.9 or 4.10) with some of the"
" new rules and technologies from Close Encounters. This is accomplished "
"using the AP Flowcharts in the last pages of this scenario book and "
"allows for the use of the following additions:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1130
msgid "• Alien Technology cards (MRB 11.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1131 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2591
msgid "• Crew cards (MRB 12.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1132 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2593
msgid "• Ship Experience (MRB 37.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1133
msgid "• Boarding Ships (MRB 19.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1134
msgid "• Security Forces (MRB 20.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1135
msgid "• Ground Combat (MRB 21.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1136
msgid "• Titans (MRB 22.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1137 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2594
msgid "• Resource cards (MRB 39.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1145
msgid ""
"Choose either Solitaire Scenario and set up the map as originally "
"indicated. Use the 30 CP Homeworld instead."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1153
msgid ""
"The following special rules apply when using Close Encounters rules in "
"Solitaire Scenarios 4.9 or 4.10:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1154
msgid ""
"• Victory Conditions remain the same as originally indicated in each "
"scenario."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1155
msgid ""
"• The AP does not use the Alien Player Victory Point Track found at the "
"back of this book; this mechanic is introduced in section 6.3.3."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1156
msgid ""
"• The AP only builds either regular fleets or Raider fleets as in the "
"original game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1157
msgid ""
"• Like the human player, the AP may now use the features listed above in "
"5.0 with the exception of Alien Technology cards, which they cannot "
"acquire."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1158
msgid "• Use the “Alien Economic Sheet” from the original game found on page 56."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1159
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 15"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1160
msgid ""
"• A Colony that is captured by the AP cannot be bombarded by the human "
"player. After all – those are your people down there! The AP will attempt"
" to defend a captured Colony with Mines, Bases, and Ground Units. The "
"defenses are purchased using points in the AP’s Defense column following "
"the AP Defense flowchart on page 61."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1161
msgid ""
"• The APs may gain technology by capturing a player Colony just like a "
"normal player would (MRB 21.13.5; MRB 21.13.6). The human player may "
"steal technology from the AP if they capture an AP Homeworld with Ground "
"Units. NOTE: This is not referring to Alien Technology cards."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1162
msgid "• Facilities (MRB 36.0) are not used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1163
msgid "• Empire Advantages (MRB 10.0) may not be used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1164
msgid "• A Flagship (MRB 23.0) may be used by the human player only."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1165
msgid ""
"• If the human player colonizes a Deep Space Barren Planet, they may gain"
" an Alien Technology card as per MRB 11.1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1171 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1480
msgid "Alien Player Behavior"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1173
msgid ""
"For AP behavior, follow the AP flowcharts starting on page 57, with the "
"following exceptions:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1174
msgid ""
"• The Econ Roll may result in an Extra Econ as per the original “Alien "
"Economic Sheet” (4.2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1175
msgid "• The AP does not colonize Barren Planets."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1176
msgid "• The AP does not have a Bank (6.5.2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1177
msgid ""
"• The AP does not launch Expansion or Extermination fleets (6.5.1). When "
"launching a non-Raider fleet, treat it like a regular fleet and stop "
"after rolling for Movement Tech on the Alien Player – Economy Phase "
"flowchart on page 57."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1178
msgid "• Regular AP fleets always target the nearest, least defended Colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1179
msgid ""
"• During ship purchasing, follow the branch for purchasing Carriers, "
"Raiders, Expansion fleets and Ground Combat units and ignore the branch "
"for Extermination fleets. This means all Regular AP fleets get a fully "
"loaded Transport for free."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1180
msgid ""
"• When using the flowcharts, ignore items specific to the Victory Point "
"scenarios (6.0). This includes the Bank, the AP’s movement, exploration "
"and colonizing rules as those are specific to the Victory Point "
"scenarios."
msgstr ""

