msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2447
msgid "Conversion Example"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2449
msgid "The Replicators have 5 RP and"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2450
msgid ""
"are attacking. The Replicators have one SW, one PD, two Type II ships, "
"and 10 unrevealed Hulls. The human player has seven Mines, three "
"Fighters, one CV, and two DDs. There is a Raider within three hexes of "
"the battle."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2451
msgid ""
"The first two steps (7.11.1.1 & 7.11.1.2) are skipped because there are "
"no unescorted non-combat ships and no lone SD, DD, or Transport."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2452
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 27"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2453
msgid ""
"Following 7.11.1.3, they convert Hulls to Scan ships. The Replicators "
"have encountered Raiders before, and since there is a Raider within three"
" hexes of the battle, the third row of the table is used. They roll a 9, "
"so two Hulls convert to a Scan ship. Eight unrevealed Hulls remain."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2454
msgid ""
"For 7.11.1.4, Hulls are converted to Minesweepers. Since there are Mines "
"in the battle and the Replicators have encountered them before, the last "
"row of the table is used. They roll a 2, so the Replicators need to have "
"enough SW ships to clear half the Mines. They have Minesweeping 2 "
"technology because they have swept three Mines previously. Since one "
"Replicator SW is already present, converting one Hull to add one more SW "
"will allow them to clear four Mines. Seven unrevealed Hulls remain."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2455
msgid ""
"For 7.11.1.5, Hulls convert to PD ships. There are three Fighters in the "
"battle and the Replicators have encountered them previously, so the fifth"
" row of the table is used. They roll a 1, but there is already a PD ship "
"present, so no additional PD ships are added."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2456
msgid ""
"Finally, in 7.11.1.6, the seven remaining unrevealed Hulls are converted "
"to three Type V ships and one Type IV ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2457
msgid ""
"The resulting Fleet is made up of one Scan ship, two SWs, one PD, two "
"Type II ships, one Type IV ship, and three Type V ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2463
msgid "Attack Priorities"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2465
msgid "Replicator ships attack according to"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2466
msgid "the priorities below."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2467
msgid "• PD ships always fire at Fighters first."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2468
msgid "• Scan ships always fire at Raiders first."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2469
msgid "• All other Replicator ships prioritize enemy ships as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2470
msgid "- Ships with the smallest Hull Size, then"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2471
msgid "- Ships with the lowest Defense Strength, then"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2472
msgid "- Ships with the highest Attack Strength, then"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2473
msgid "- Ships that have not yet fired."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2481
msgid "The Replicators never screen their ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2482
msgid ""
"However, Replicator Scan ships and SW ships can only be fired upon if the"
" human player has more ships present than the Replicators. In any case, "
"Replicator Scan ships and SW ships can fire normally."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2488
msgid "Retreat"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2490
msgid "Replicator ships will retreat (when eligible) if"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2491
msgid ""
"the human player has three times as many Hull Points (or more) in the "
"battle. As noted in 7.8.2, a human player Base counts as double (6 Hull "
"Points)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2492
msgid "The Replicator Flagship will always retreat if it has taken 2 damage."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2498
msgid "Replicator Economic Phase"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2500
msgid ""
"Each Full Replicator Colony produces one Hull. No ship type is chosen at "
"the time of production. The Replicator can carry over more than 30 CP per"
" turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2506
msgid "Production/Development"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2508
msgid "The Replicators will produce"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2509
msgid "Hulls and develop technologies as indicated below (cost permitting)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2510
msgid ""
"In Economic Phases 1-3, the Replicators will buy one extra Hull at their "
"Homeworld for 8 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2511
msgid "Starting with Economic Phase 4 and thereafter:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2512
msgid ""
"• If they have the Fast Replicators Empire Advantage and have Move 5 "
"technology or lower, buy the next level of Move technology for 15 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2513
msgid ""
"• If they have the Advanced Research Replicators Empire Advantage, buy "
"one RP for 25 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2514
msgid ""
"• If they have the Replicator Capitol Empire Advantage, buy one extra "
"Hull for 8 CP and place it at the Replicator Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2515
msgid "• In all other cases, when 8 CP or more are available, roll a die:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2516
msgid ""
"- 1-4: Buy one extra Hull for 8 CP and place it at the Replicator "
"Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2517
msgid "- 5-8: Buy one RP for 30 CP (25 CP for Advanced Research Replicators)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2518
msgid ""
"- 9-10: Buy next level of Move technology for 20 CP (15 CP for Fast "
"Replicators)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2519
msgid ""
"• Otherwise, if Deep Space is fully explored, no Minerals remain on the "
"map, and the Replicators cannot make their required purchase, buy one "
"extra Hull for 8 CP and place it at the Replicator Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2525
msgid "Replicators Standard"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2527
msgid ""
"A half-hex on the right edge sometimes needs to be in play to fit all 26 "
"Home System markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2528
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 28"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2534
msgid "Replicators Large"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2536
msgid "COOPERATIVE SCENARIOS"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2537
msgid ""
"These scenarios were designed by an avid fan and playtester of Space "
"Empires to allow players to play against “the game” rather than each "
"other. These scenarios are ideal for teaching the original game and Close"
" Encounters to new players. They are also ideal for playing with "
"significant others that might not take too kindly to direct conflict."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2543 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2988
