#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3304
msgid "AP Bot"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3311
msgid "Purpose"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3313
msgid ""
"Solitaire and Coop is an important element of Space Empires 4x gameplay "
"that has evolved over the 10 years of the system’s existence. The "
"original scenario types, particularly DM, can feel a bit like a “tower "
"defense” game, which can be a fun style of play. However, we aim to "
"improve on surprising the player in this new mode by making the AP act "
"more like a player substitute or “bot”. We hope that, like a player, the "
"AP Bot can surprise you. This AP bot can effectively be used in (almost) "
"any previously published scenario with a wide variety of optional rules. "
"Treat this set of rules as completely different and not connected at all "
"to the previously published (above) solo/Coop scenarios. Note: The "
"flowcharts at the end of this scenario book apply to the rule sections "
"above. They do NOT apply to this iteration of the AP Bot."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3319
msgid "Definitions"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3321
msgid ""
"• 1d100: Two 10 sided dice rolled using one die as the 10s digit and the "
"other as the 1s digit, generating a number from 1 through 100."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3322
msgid "• AP: The AP and AP bot are used interchangeably in this rule set"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3323
msgid "• EV: Exploration Vessel"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3324
msgid "• FOB: Forward Operating Base"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3325
msgid "• HS: Home System"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3326
msgid ""
"• Known AP Fleet: Ships in known AP Fleets have their technology levels "
"tracked on a spare Production Sheet. There are situations in the game "
"where a Known AP Fleet can become Unknown again and thus, information on "
"the Production Sheet may no longer be true since the AP Fleet will get to"
" do Tech and Ship buying again."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3327
msgid ""
"• Map Size: the number of DS hexes following the shortest route between "
"the AP and the nearest Player HS at the start of the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3328
msgid "• Player: Human player."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3329
msgid "• SCT: Special Counter Tech."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3330
msgid ""
"• Unknown AP Fleet: An Alien Player fleet that is face down whose units "
"and technology are unknown to the human players."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3336
msgid "Prime Directive"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3338
msgid ""
"• The AP’s “AI” might be a primitive life form, but we are (as usual per "
"Trek) not avoiding contact in this wargame. The Prime Directive in Space "
"Empires actually means: Where the rules are silent or conflict, use "
"common sense and play your opponent intelligently. This rule supersedes "
"all other rulings. This is most likely to apply if many optional rules "
"are in use (such as Alien Technology and Empire Advantage cards) for "
"which complex rulings are not possible or practical."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3339
msgid ""
"• So as not to derail other systems in play, do not alter the AP’s "
"Strategy and similar functions after employing the Prime Directive."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3340
msgid ""
"• Example: The AP should build SCs because it has the SC Rush strategy, "
"but it was just revealed that they have a Crew Card for CAs and an Alien "
"Technology card for CAs, and they could reasonably field well equipped "
"CAs. The AP would build CAs instead. They are kept as having the “SC "
"Rush” strategy for now for all other purposes so as not to derail other "
"systems."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3346
msgid "Scenarios"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3348
msgid ""
"• The revised AP is meant to be able to substitute for a human player in "
"most scenarios (i.e. CSB 2.2 2-Player Standard)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3349
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 34"
msgstr ""

