msgid ">8"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3370
msgid "First Player"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3372
msgid ""
"The first player in AP games is decided randomly as per MRB 3.0. The AP "
"and DM have their own rules for bidding below. Regardless of who is the "
"first player, the AP always resolves their Econ Phase functions after the"
" players resolve their Econ Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3378
msgid "New Hidden Galactic Capitol Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3380
msgid ""
"• These rules represent a new scenario where the GC is hidden at the "
"start. The AP Bot may be used with almost any previous scenario and does "
"not require this scenario."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3381
msgid ""
"• Features: The GC represents an ancient, super-advanced civilization. It"
" has a 5 CP colony counter on it. It will generate Militia if attacked "
"and will lose levels if bombarded like a Colony. It will also grow a "
"level at the end of every Econ Phase if it has been bombarded below the 5"
" CP level. Human players may not attack a GC but combat with the AP may "
"occur in the GC hex. Human players may place ground troops on the GC "
"which will fight alongside the GC Militia to defend against AP invasion."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3382
msgid ""
"• GC Discovery: The GC’s location is not known at the start of the game. "
"The GC counter is seeded into an assortment of Deep Space markers "
"randomly placed near the human players."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3383
msgid ""
"• The GC will randomly appear along the edge of a human player’s Home "
"System markers. Set aside the GC counter when assembling the random Deep "
"Space counters for a scenario. Also set aside 9 random Deep Space "
"counters. The GC is added face down, at random to the separated Deep "
"Space counters. If the scenario in use has fewer than 9 DS border hexes, "
"remove random non-GC counters from the mix to achieve the correct number "
"of border hexes."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3384
msgid ""
"• Place these separate DS counters adjacent to your HS. If playing with "
"more than 1 human player, distribute them such that they are as "
"equidistant as possible from each HS edge. If playing solitaire, place "
"them in the first row of DS hexes centering to your HW."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3385
msgid ""
"• GC Trade: Human players may trade with the GC by extending their MS "
"Pipelines to the GC hex as if it were one of their colonies. Instead of "
"gaining 1 CP for this colony, human players receive 5 CP per Econ Phase. "
"Multiple human players may benefit from this at the same time if their MS"
" Pipeline path is complete. Optionally, players using other GC scenarios "
"may replace the economic gain with this rule instead."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3386
msgid ""
"• GC Loss Condition: If the GC is captured or eliminated, the Players "
"lose just as if their own HW had been captured or eliminated."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3387
msgid "• Deep Space DMs: Never attack the Galactic Capitol."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3393
msgid "Lost in Space Resolution"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3395
msgid "See 1.1.9."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3401
msgid "Regional Map Resolution"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3403
msgid ""
"Instead, for AP or players, flip and resolve all eligible adjacent hexes "
"as if flipped by Exploration technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3409
msgid "Player Alliance Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3411
msgid ""
"Players need not use an alliance rule, and may play against each other, "
"if using the revised AP bot rules. AP information is still shared and "
"tracked publicly for all Players to see, and the AP treats all Players as"
" if they were allied."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3417
msgid "AP Alliances"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3419
msgid ""
"The APs always have an UNEASY ALLIANCE but also do not share information."
" They operate completely separately from each other."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3425
msgid "Victory Points"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3427
msgid ""
"The AP scenarios no longer use victory points. Although the Colony Point "
"rule (CSB 1.1.7) may be used instead of HW elimination. However, there is"
" a chance the AP bot concedes if losing HS colonies. Difficulty settings "
"are described below."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3435
msgid ""
"If used, the AP may randomly select the Galactic Capital as if it were "
"another player HW for Extermination. If the GC is captured or eliminated,"
" the AP wins."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3441
msgid "Number of Alien Players"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3443
msgid ""
"The number of alien players in general should equal the number of human "
"players. Use the appropriate scenario map. For a particularly challenging"
" solitaire or two player game, challenge one additional AP. If you do, "
"consider decreasing the Difficulty by one step (So Normal becomes Easy)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3444
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 35"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3450
msgid "Alien Intelligence and Economy"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3452
msgid ""
"Like previous scenarios, the AP generates CP, does research, and builds "
"fleets using tables which are revised below. The AP performs Econ rolls "
"like prior AP scenarios. The amount of CP allocated per roll is always "
"10. There is also a difference between rolls for CP generated from the "
"HS, called HS rolls, versus Deep Space colonies, called DS rolls. The "
"base number of HS rolls an AP gets is determined by the Difficulty, "
"Player HW size and use of Facilities (RC/ICs). The AP has two budgets, "
"one for Fleet and one for Technology spending. AP Fleet/Tech budgets may "
"go into the negative due to game events (i.e. certain resource cards). If"
" the AP is attempting to spend out of a budget with insufficient funds, "
"see below, as the AP’s Fleet Budget will take from the Tech budget to "
"launch certain fleets. The AP Tracks Economy on new Economic Sheets (like"
" human Players). It tracks revealed ships and technology as a player on a"
" normal production sheet, including the highest Movement technology used "
"by all Players."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3453
msgid ""
"• HS Rolls: The number of dice rolled representing CP from the AP’s HS, "
"including Barren planet. Game difficulty and certain options sets the "
"Base HS Rolls. Base HS Rolls are increased when the AP obtains its HS "
"barren planet and then the number of HS rolls may be modified by Missing "
"Colonies, Maintenance and Missing HW (see below). The minimum number of "
"HS rolls is 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3454
msgid "Options Base HS Rolls"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3455 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3479
msgid "20 CP Player HW without Facilities"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3456
msgid "30 CP Player HW 7"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3457 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3480
msgid "Player using Facilities"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3458
msgid "Difficulty Modify Base HS Rolls by"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3460 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3482
msgid "-1 HS Roll"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3462
msgid "+0 HS Roll"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3464 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3484
msgid "+1 HS Roll"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3466
msgid "+2 HS Rolls"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3468 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3486
msgid "+3 HS Rolls"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3470
msgid "+4 HS Rolls"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3471
msgid ""
"• DS Rolls: DS colonies generate separate rolls for CP. Only non- "
"blockaded colonies generate a DS roll. A DS roll is generated for "
"producing colonies regardless of level and the CP value is always as if "
"full. This is usually 5 CP but card effects or planetary attributes (if "
"used) may modify this value."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3472
msgid ""
"• Terraforming 2 in Nebula each counts as a DS roll worth 5 CP. MS "
"Pipelines are not needed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3473
msgid ""
"• Insufficient funds in budget: Unlike in previous scenarios, any time "
"the AP is attempting to purchase something from the Fleet budget but has "
"insufficient funds, the remainder is taken from the Tech budget instead, "
"if available. However, the reverse is not true: if insufficient funds are"
" present in the Tech budget, that purchase is not made, no funds are "
"taken from the Fleet budget."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3474
msgid ""
"• Expansion Fleet launch: If the Fleet budget does not have at least 60 "
"CP and the AP is attempting to launch a fleet, funds are immediately "
"taken from the Tech budget to get to exactly 60 Fleet CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3475
msgid ""
"• The AP gains knowledge of Player technology as a normal player would, "
"through combat, and the AP’s knowledge is updated at the end of a battle."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3476
msgid ""
"• Optionally, you may keep the AP blind to Player technology revealed "
"only through NPA combat. Likewise, there is a system in 13.53 for "
"resolving AP battles against NPA planets without generating (and "
"revealing) AP technology, thus also keeping the Player blind to AP "
"technology early on."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3492
msgid "Misc Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3494
msgid "• Black Hole Jumping is not used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3495
msgid "• DS DMs may behave differently when revealed by an EV."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3496
msgid ""
"• Non-player Aliens may be used. The new NPA ships from All Good Things "
"and Deep Space Planet Attributes may be used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3497
msgid ""
"• Alien Player Starting Technology: Unlike previous AP rules, the AP gets"
" the same starting technologies as a human player."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3498
msgid ""
"• AP Fleets: With the exception of the EV and SCX, all mobile AP units "
"exist in Fleets. The Fleet tracking markers may be used to track, but do "
"not limit the number of fleets. Units within a Fleet are never split off "
"with the exception of Extermination Fleet “shell game” Decoys. Fleets may"
" be merged in some circumstances."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3499
msgid ""
"• Exploration Vessel: The AP has a special Exploration Vessel (EV) that "
"functions differently from other ships in the game. It is a non-combat "
"ship. It is not considered a fleet nor is it ever part of one. It is "
"represented on the map by a Miner. It can move 1 hex per turn. The AP "
"receives a number of EVs at game start for free based on Map Size, see "
"Expansion Goals Table, 13.4.1. The AP may replace lost EVs and this costs"
" 5 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3500
msgid ""
"• Player At-Start Forces: Per scenario rules (i.e. typical is 3xSC, 3x "
"Colony Ship, 1xMiner, 4xSY unless otherwise specified in chosen "
"scenario). Players may use Flagships. If they do the AP also uses "
"Flagships. The players do not start with any additional technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3501
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 36"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3502
msgid ""
"• Unlike prior AP scenarios, the AP gets almost nothing “for free” and "
"all technology and ships are purchased the same way a Player would. The "
"AP is limited by the number of ship counters as a normal Player."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3508 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3788
msgid "Reaction Movement"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3510
msgid ""
"• AP Fleets use Reaction movement differently if Exploration 2 is "
"researched."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3511
msgid ""
"• All units within a Known or Unknown Fleet are eligible for Reaction "
"movement if Exploration 2 and Move 4 are researched, regardless of ship "
"types in the fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3512
msgid ""
"• When Exploration 2 is researched all AP Fleets are immediately equipped"
" with it."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3513
msgid ""
"• All AP HS hexes can count as a battle hex containing friendly units, "
"regardless of the presence or absence of friendly units in that hex. "
"Thus, AP fleets in friendly HS can Reaction move into any HS hex "
"containing enemy units."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3514
msgid ""
"• Advanced Comm Array affects all AP fleets, regardless of ship types in "
"the fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3520
msgid "Paranoia"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3522
msgid ""
"• Paranoia is a new statistic introduced to track the AP’s "
"“understanding” of the game state. This roughly measures how poorly a "
"game is going for the AP. The more Paranoia rises, the more likely the AP"
" will attempt something unconventional or unexpected. The idea is to keep"
" human players on their toes and make the AP less predictable."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3523
msgid ""
"• This statistic is tracked on the AP Bot PAC with a counter matching the"
" AP’s color."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3524
msgid "• Paranoia level starts at 1 and never goes above 10 or below 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3530
msgid "Increasing Paranoia Level"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3532
msgid ""
"• Paranoia Level is increased by one, immediately, each time certain "
"events caused by Players occur as listed below. Only Player interactions "
"can trigger Paranoia level changes (e.g. losing a battle against an NPA "
"does not increase Paranoia)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3533
msgid "• AP loses a colony to a Player (colony eliminated or captured)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3534
msgid ""
"• Player-initiated battle occurs in AP HS Colony or HW. Bombardment of a "
"colony without combat does not count as a battle."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3535
msgid ""
"• AP lost a battle against a Player: AP was eliminated or retreated non-"
"BC ships. Losing only an EV does not count."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3536
msgid ""
"At end of battle: The AP lost sufficient Key Ships in one battle based on"
" its Strategy. This only triggers once per battle. Captured ships never "
"count as lost key ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3537
msgid "Strategy Key Ship"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3538 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3556
