msgid "Yarr!"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3551 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3563
msgid "BD x2"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3552
msgid "Alternate Empire"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3553
msgid "MB x2"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3569
msgid "Decreasing Paranoia Level"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3571
msgid ""
"• Paranoia is only reduced by Resetting (below) or may be reduced by 1 "
"(minimum Paranoia level is 1) when any of the following occur:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3572
msgid ""
"• The AP won a battle against a Player (the Player retreated or was "
"destroyed)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3573
msgid "• The AP destroyed or captured an enemy HS colony (not just blockaded)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3574
msgid "• The AP rebuilt to max CP a previously destroyed friendly HS colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3580
msgid "Paranoia Checks"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3582
msgid ""
"• Some game events, such as encountering an Unknown AP Fleet, trigger a "
"Paranoia Check that may change the AP’s behavior."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3583
msgid ""
"• Roll 1d100. If the result is equal to or less than the corresponding "
"1d100 Paranoia value for the AP on the Paranoia/Morale Track, the AP "
"FAILS its Paranoia Check. Otherwise, the AP passes its Paranoia Check and"
" these results have different effects depending on what triggered the "
"check."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3584
msgid ""
"• Since Paranoia Checks roughly estimate how well the AP thinks it is "
"winning, they may be substituted for situations in which the Players are "
"uncertain how the AP will deal with an edge case or interaction, not "
"specifically covered in these rules. Determine which decision would be "
"the most defensive and make that occur on a failed Paranoia check. "
"Otherwise, consider the Prime Directive."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3585
msgid ""
"• Paranoia Reset: If a Paranoia Check changes a Fleet’s Strategy, the "
"Paranoia level resets (to 1). When the Paranoia Check automatically fails"
" on the first Fleet Generation, Paranoia is not reset."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3591
msgid "Morale"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3593
msgid ""
"• Morale is tracked similar to Paranoia but is only relevant to the "
"current battle. See below."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3594
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 37"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3600
msgid "Forward Operating Base (FOB)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3602
msgid ""
"• For the AP, SY markers are Forward Operating Bases (FOB). They are kept"
" face down until encountered. They represent Player knowledge that this "
"colony has sufficient capacity to launch any fleet. This designation will"
" also play a role if one of these colonies is attacked. Although FOBs "
"usually only appear when a Fleet Launch does not occur, new FOBs are "
"immediately available for Fleet Launches this EP if a game event dictates"
" otherwise (it was in development for a few turns but the Players only "
"just now found out about it)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3608
msgid "AP Setup"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3610
msgid ""
"• Alien Player HW Location: For scenarios where the player chooses which "
"hex to place the HW, the AP places it in the most central hex possible."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3611
msgid ""
"• Flagships: If Players use Flagships, the AP will also use a Flagship, "
"but these do not appear until Unknown Fleet Generation (see below)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3612
msgid ""
"• AP HS Markers: All AP HS markers, except the HW, remain face-down "
"initially. AP units may move through these face down markers as if they "
"were empty hexes. These are all revealed in the Econ Phase that the AP "
"makes its first Econ roll or when an enemy ship enters the AP HS. Place "
"full 5 CP colonies on all colonizable planets, including the barren "
"planet if Terraforming has been researched. Remove all Minerals (these "
"are already accounted for in the AP’s economy). For defense and movement "
"purposes, the AP treats any face down HS marker as if it were a HS "
"colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3613
msgid ""
"• Distribute 120 CP to Tech budget and 30 CP to Fleet Budget. The AP’s "
"economy can otherwise be ignored until Econ rolls are first triggered, "
"usually in EP 5. These values are already listed in Carry Over on the AP "
"Bot Production sheet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3614
msgid ""
"• If the AP’s listed Goal DS Colonies (see Expansion Goals Table, 13.4.1)"
" is not zero, purchase Exploration 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3620
msgid "AP Econ Phase"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3622
msgid ""
"• Most AP Econ Phase events are skipped, including all Econ rolls, until "
"Econ Phase 5 unless a Player unit has come to within 2 hexes of AP HS. In"
" this case, the AP begins performing Econ Phase events including Econ "
"rolls as if it were Econ Phase 5."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3623
msgid ""
"• If this is the first Econ Phase the AP is resolving, reveal all AP HS "
"markers and place colonies as described in the previous section."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3624
msgid ""
"• Econ Phase 5 and Every Econ Phase Thereafter: Follow these steps in "
"order."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3625
msgid ""
"• Starting EVs: Before EP 5’s movement turns, place the number of "
"starting EVs (per Expansion Goals Table, 13.4.1). These are placed for "
"free."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3626
msgid ""
"• EV Placement: The first EV is placed on the AP HS hex closest to the "
"nearest Player HW. Any remaining EVs are placed on a random HS hex in the"
" same row as the first EV. In some"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3627
msgid ""
"scenarios, such as 4 Player, the remaining EVs are instead placed within "
"a random HS hex within 2 hexes of the first EV."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3628
msgid ""
"• Colonize Barren: If Terraforming 1 has been researched and AP HS "
"markers are face-up, place a full colony marker on the Barren planet. "
"Regardless, once Terraforming 1 is researched the AP gains +1 base HS "
"Roll for the remainder of the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3629
msgid ""
"• Econ Rolls: After Players have resolved their EP, calculate Total HS "
"and DS Rolls and assign to budget, adding any carry over. Each HS die "
"rolled generates 10 CP for either Fleet or Tech budget based on the roll "
"result: 1-7 is Fleet, 8-10 is Tech."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3630
msgid "• HS Rolls: Modify HS rolls by the following. Minimum 1 roll."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3631
msgid ""
"- Missing Colonies: Lost, Damaged or Blockaded HS colonies. Each Missing "
"Colony reduces the number of HS rolls by 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3632
msgid "- Maintenance: Reduce HS rolls by 1 for every AP fleet on the board."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3633
msgid ""
"- Missing HW: If HW blockaded or damaged, reduce HS rolls by 2. Only full"
" HW counts as normal."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3634
msgid ""
"DS Minerals: Perform a one-time extra HS Roll for every DS Mineral towed "
"to an AP colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3635
msgid ""
"• DS Rolls: DS Colonies generate CP for Fleet/Tech budgets similar to "
"Econ Rolls but always generate its full value (typically 5 CP) per roll. "
"Mined Nebula also generate DS Rolls typically 5 CP in value. Game events "
"may yield higher or lower full colony CP values."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3636
msgid ""
"• Launch Colony Ship: If no enemies are present in AP HS and the AP has "
"an empty HS planet (due to colony elimination) it will purchase a Colony "
"Ship and send it to that planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3637
msgid ""
"• Use Space Wreck: If a Space Wreck has been towed to an AP colony set it"
" aside. When generating the next Unknown AP Fleet, roll for Space Wreck, "
"adding the technology as a normal Player."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3638
msgid ""
"• Purchase EV: If the AP has below min EVs (see Expansion Goals Table, "
"13.4.1) and has not achieved Goal DS colonies, the AP purchases an EV for"
" 5 CP and places on a random HS hex closest to the Player’s home system. "
"If insufficient CP is available, skip this step and the AP will re-"
"attempt next Econ Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3639
msgid ""
"• Exploration Technology: Make a Paranoia check. On a fail, purchase the "
"next level of Exploration technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3640
msgid ""
"• Terraforming Technology: The AP attempts to purchase up to its max "
"Terraforming technology (see Expansion Goals Table). It never buys "
"Terraforming technology above the listed maximum. Make a Paranoia Check. "
"On a fail, skip this section. On a pass:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3641
msgid ""
"- If Terraforming 0: The AP purchases the next level of Terraforming (if "
"able). Skip the rest of this section."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3642
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 38"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3643
msgid ""
"- If Terraforming 1: The AP purchases the next level of Terraforming (if "
"able)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3644
msgid ""
"- If Terraforming 2 has been purchased and unmined Nebula exist in the "
"HS: purchase 1 Miner. Place Miner on unmined HS Nebula starting with the "
"closest to the HW. Skip the rest of this section. If AP HS is still face-"
"down (because of optional rule 13.55), set Miner aside for now. It is "
"still functional, but its location is unknown until AP HS is face- up."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3645
msgid ""
"- If Terraforming 2 and an unmined DS Nebula exist within 2 hexes of AP "
"HS: Purchase a Miner and place it in such a DS Nebula. Each generates +1 "
"DS roll as above. This is skipped if Player units Threaten this Nebula."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3646
msgid ""
"• Military Academy: If in use and AP HS or DS colonies Threatened, make a"
" Paranoia Check. On a Fail, purchase the next level of Military Academy. "
"On a Pass, do not."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3647
msgid ""
"• Bid for Turn Order: Turn order bid occurs if either the AP Fleet, EV, "
"colonies, or HS are Threatened. If none of the above are Threatened, make"
" a Paranoia Check. On a Fail, the AP bids anyway. Otherwise, the AP bids "
"zero. The CP bid is based on the lowest of two d10 rolls, however, the "
"dice may explode such that larger values are possible. Perform the "
"following:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3648
msgid "- Roll two d10s."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3649
msgid ""
"- If doubles are rolled, roll 1d10 and add this value to one of the "
"initial die values."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3650
msgid ""
"- If any subsequent roll was again the same value, repeat this process, "
"adding the value to the initial die value each time."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3651
msgid ""
"- When no more duplicate values are rolled, the resulting bid is the "
"summed value."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3652
msgid ""
"- If no doubles were initially rolled, take the lower of the two dice, "
"subtract 3 then add the current Paranoia Level. The result is the CP bid."
" If the result is 0 or less, no CP is bid."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3653
msgid "- Deduct the bid amount from the higher of Fleet or Tech budgets."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3654
msgid ""
"Example: A 7 and 7 are rolled. Another 1d10 is rolled and results again "
"in 7. Another 1d10 is rolled but this comes up as a 2. The final bid is "
"7+7+2 = 16."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3655
msgid ""
"Example: A 7 and 8 are rolled. The current Paranoia Level is 2. The final"
" bid is 7 – 3 + 2 = 5."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3656
msgid ""
"• Check for Fleet Launch: If the AP has not yet achieved its Goal DS "
"Colonies and no Expansion Fleet is on the board, an Expansion Fleet is "
"automatically launched. Otherwise, roll 1d10 and modify per below. If the"
" result is 8 or less proceed to Fleet Launch."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3657
msgid "- Add 1 to the result for every fleet on the board."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3658
msgid ""
"- Reduce the roll by the difference in number of current AP DS colonies "
"vs goal DS colonies. (e.g. The AP with 1 DS colony on a 6 size map would "
"subtract 1 from the roll)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3659
msgid ""
"- An unmodified roll of 1 is always a launch, an unmodified roll of 10 is"
" never a launch."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3660
msgid "• Construct Forward Operating Base:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3661
msgid ""
"- If no Fleet Launch occurred, the AP attempts to develop a colony into a"
" Forward Operating Base (FOB). Place an FOB on an unblockaded, full CP DS"
" colony that does not already have one. If no DS colony is available and "
"less than 2 HS colonies have a FOB, randomly place the FOB either on the "
"unblockaded, full HS colony nearest to deep space and closest to the "
"center of the map or on the unblockaded, full HS colony nearest to DS but"
" furthest from center of the map."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3662
msgid ""
"- If HS markers are still face-down, set the FOB aside and place it as "
"above as soon as HS markers become face up. It will not be used until "
"then."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3663
msgid ""
"- The AP never establishes more than 2 HS FOB. No colony can have more "
"than 1 FOB on it. The HW can never be an FOB, it is assumed to have all "
"shipyard capabilities it needs. If no eligible colony is available, no "
"FOB is placed. The AP never actually places SY units that would take part"
" in combat or count towards ship construction. If an FOB is lost (due to "
"losing space combat at a colony), remove this SY marker."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3664
msgid "- If an FOB was placed, spend 20 CP from the Fleet budget."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3665
msgid "- If no eligible hex for placement, skip FOB construction."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3666
msgid ""
"- If the AP can build Advanced Bases, has not built an Advanced Base in a"
" DS non-planet hex and it attempted FOB but there were no DS or HS "
"colonies eligible to be FOB this Econ Phase as above, it will build an "
"Advanced Base. Select a hex most likely to act as a choke point in terms "
"of terrain (see Fall Back below), preferring DS hexes closer to HS, and "
"purchase the Advanced Base. The AP ignores the MS requirement. This is "
"placed face up since Players already know about it."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3667
msgid ""
"• Grow Colonies: Grow all colonies as per a normal player at the end of "
"the AP Econ Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3668
msgid ""
"• Check for AP Concession: In addition to losing if the AP’s HW is lost, "
"the AP may concede victory. If 3 or more AP HS colonies have been "
"eliminated or captured (not just blockaded), perform a Paranoia Check. On"
" fail, the AP concedes. On a pass, they press on."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3669
msgid ""
"• Beyond Econ Phase 20: Continue performing EPs as above using a new "
"sheet if needed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3675
msgid "AP Fleet Launch"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3677
msgid ""
"• If the Fleet Budget has at least 120 CP, this may be an Extermination "
"Fleet (A killer fleet designed to crush the GC or Player HW). Otherwise, "
"this is an Expansion Fleet (A fleet designed to get more colonies). CP "
"may be taken from the Tech budget to launch an Expansion Fleet, see "
"above."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3678
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 39"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3679
msgid ""
"• CP Allocation: The current Fleet budget CP value is allocated to the "
"Fleet. The amount of CP in the Fleet CP budget is assigned to the Fleet "
"and subtracted from the Fleet CP Budget. In the Fleets section of the AP "
"Economic Sheet write the Type of fleet followed by the allocated CP. "
"Write the Move Technology level once generated (below). Example: Write "
"“1st Expansion Fleet [80] Move 2” with the bracketed number being the "
"assigned Fleet CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3680
msgid ""
"• Possible Movement Tech Purchase: If the Technology budget has at least "
"60 CP, Movement tech may be purchased."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3681
msgid ""
"- If Move 4 has not been researched, always purchase one level of "
"Movement technology. Then, if Move 4 is still not researched, roll 1d10 "
"and compare the die result to the Move Tech Chance for this Map Size (see"
" Expansion Goals Table, 13.4.1). If the result is equal to or less than "
"the listed value, purchase another level of Movement technology. A roll "
"of 1 is always a purchase, a roll of 10 is never a purchase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3682
msgid ""
"- If Move 4 has been researched, perform the roll as above to see if one "
"level of Movement technology will be purchased."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3683
msgid ""
"• Place Fleet: If enemy ships are in or adjacent to the AP HS, launch the"
" fleet at the HW. Otherwise, make a Paranoia check. On a pass, launch the"
" fleet at the closest FOB to enemy Player, choose randomly if tied or HW "
"if no FOB available. On a fail, launch from the HW. Fleets cannot be "
"launched from blockaded HW or FOB. If the destination is unavailable, "
"place the fleet in the nearest available eligible hex (i.e. the HW or "
"another FOB), otherwise the launch is canceled."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3684
msgid ""
"• Extermination Fleet Target: If this is an extermination fleet, select a"
" random HW/GC as the current target. The target may change later."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3690
msgid "AP Movement Turn"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3692
msgid ""
"• Prior to moving, the AP first determines any current Threats, "
"Detrimental Terrain and sets Posture. Then a Destination Check is "
"performed for each Fleet in which eligible destination hexes are "
"determined. From that pool of eligible hexes, one is selected based on "
"Restrictions and Priorities for the current Posture. If, after applying "
"Restrictions and Priorities, no eligible hexes remain, attempt the next "
"Destination Check down to determine different eligible destination hexes."
" If no other Destination Checks are possible for current Posture, the "
"Fleet/EV remains stationary."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3693
msgid ""
"• Determine Threats: The AP tracks the highest level of Player Movement "
"tech and Fast tech demonstrated on the Production sheet. When any Player "
"moves with a higher Movement tech for the first time, mark this on the AP"
" Production sheet. This is not tracked separately for individual Players."
" A hex is Threatened if Player combat-capable units, face down Player "
"units, DMs, hostile Pirates or Amoebas are able to move to, or are "
"already in, that hex on their next movement turn. The AP judges Player’s "
"ability to move to a given hex based on known Movement and Fast "
"technology. It assumes all face- down Player units could equip Fast, if "
"known. It will also take Fast into consideration on Turn 1. It will not "
"take Black Hole"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3694
msgid ""
"Sling Shot of an enemy fleet into consideration. The AP ignores units "
"already present in the destination hex if the move is part of an Attack a"
" Fleet or Attack HW/GC Destination Check."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3695
msgid ""
"• Identify Detrimental Terrain: Terrain is detrimental if it would put an"
" AP Fleet at a combat disadvantage. Detrimental Terrain either reduces "
"the odds the AP enters that hex or forbids entry entirely depending on "
"game circumstances. Consider the Prime Directive of game effects such as "
"scenario cards that alter terrain behavior. This is informed by the "
"Player’s knowledge of current AP technology. The following count as "
"Detrimental Terrain if:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3696
msgid "- Asteroid: AP lacks Tactics or AP has Attack > Defense tech."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3697
msgid ""
"- Nebula: AP lacks Tactics or AP has Defense > Attack tech. Entry "
"forbidden for Raider Strategy."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3698
msgid ""
"- Quantum Filament: AP has < Move 4 tech. Entry forbidden for Fighter, "
"Raider, or Yarr! Strategy."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3699
msgid "- Quasar: AP has Defense > Attack tech."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3700
msgid "- Pulsar: Forbidden for Hit and Run BC or Horsemen of the Plains."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3701
msgid "- Plasma Storm: Entry forbidden for SC rush, Fighter Strategy."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3702
msgid ""
"- Black Hole: Entry forbidden except by certain Destination Checks that "
"permit entry."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3703
msgid ""
"• Posture: If any AP Fleet (excluding EV) is Threatened, make a Paranoia "
"Check. If the Check fails, Posture is Defense. If it succeeds or if no "
"Fleet is Threatened, Posture is Offense."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3704
msgid ""
"• Destination Check: To determine eligible movement hexes, each AP "
"Fleet/EV, performs a Destination Check every chance one would move unless"
" instructed to do otherwise. Criteria are given below and followed in "
"order. If one check fails, move on to the next for current Posture. "
"Closeness is determined by the minimum number of EPs it would take the "
"mover to reach the destination. Roll randomly for ties and consider the "
"Prime Directive. EV movement resolution occurs before Fleets. The order "
"of movement resolution beyond this should consider the Prime Directive."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3705
msgid "• Exploration Vessel and SCX:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3706
msgid ""
"- For movement purposes, EVs are in Exploring mode or Mining mode which "
"is independent of Posture. EVs/SCXs are the only AP ship that interacts "
"with Minerals or Space Wrecks."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3707
msgid ""
"- Exploration before moving: If Exploration 1 is researched, regardless "
"of mode, the Exploration Vessel reveals an adjacent unexplored Deep Space"
" marker as if it was equipped with Exploration 1. The marker is flipped "
"over for all Players to see and may be eliminated as per Exploration "
"Technology. If DS DMs are used, reveal the DM but it does not act until "
"the first time a combat-capable ship or AP fleet becomes adjacent to it. "
"If multiple, adjacent unexplored Deep Space Markers are available, the "
"Destination Check dictates the preferred"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3708
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 40"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3709
msgid ""
"marker to be explored, exploring the furthest marker from AP HS (or "
"randomly on ties) if no preference given."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3710
msgid ""
"- If Exploration 1 is not researched, no exploration tech action occurs, "
"and the EV is permitted instead to enter an unexplored DS hex as per "
"certain Destination Checks below."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3711
msgid "- Destination Check (Exploring):"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3712
msgid ""
"1. Find DS Planets: If AP has fewer DS colonies than Goal DS Colonies, "
"prefer using Exploration tech on markers closest to AP HS then move to "
"maximize adjacency to unexplored DS markers that are closest to AP HS "
"(randomly on ties) which could include remaining stationary."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3713
msgid ""
"2. Adjacent to Mineral/Space Wreck: If with or adjacent to unclaimed DS "
"Mineral/Space Wreck, switch to Mining mode."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3714
msgid ""
"3. Retreat from enemy HS: If adjacent to enemy HS, move closer to a "
"friendly HS."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3715
msgid ""
"4. Find Path to Player: If AP has DS Colonies ≥ Goal DS Colonies, move to"
" maximize adjacency to unexplored DS markers that are farthest from AP HS"
" which could include remaining stationary."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3716
msgid "- Destination Check (Mining):"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3717
msgid ""
"1. Adjacent to Mineral/Space Wreck: If the EV switched to Mining mode "
"from resolving Destination Check, move into the adjacent DS Mineral/Space"
" Wreck hex. It is now towing for future moves. If multiple adjacent are "
"available, it selects the one furthest from its HS."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3718
msgid ""
"2. Towing: Tow Mineral/Space Wreck to the nearest colony or HW, as a "
"normal Miner. If AP HS markers are still face-down, it will tow to the "
"nearest face-down AP HS marker and drop off there. Once the payload has "
"been dropped off, the EV will re-enter Exploring mode."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3719
msgid ""
"• SCX: If the AP has researched Advanced Construction 3, it will purchase"
" and place an SCX during the next Econ Phase in which it has sufficient "
"Fleet budget CP. This SCX behaves exactly as an EV (including mining) but"
" with the movement technology bonuses for an SCX. Place on furthest FOB "
"from HW or HW if unavailable. If encountered in combat, it fights as an "
"SCX and is not eliminated as a non-Combat ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3720
msgid ""
"• Restrictions and Priorities: EVs ignore Detrimental Terrain descriptors"
" as above and instead use the following only. The EV never intentionally "
"enters an enemy/pirate/NPA occupied hex, black hole, plasma/ion storm or "
"a Threatened hex. It will avoid moving to a DS hex adjacent to a storm "
"hex in the third movement turn. It only enters an unexplored DS hex as "
"permitted above. Prioritize first destinations that can be reached this "
"EP, then hexes that bring it closer to DS Minerals/ Space Wrecks."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3728
msgid "• The primary goal of an Expansion Fleet is to take NPA planets."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3729 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3749
msgid ""
"• Destination Check (Offense): First, if this fleet is in or adjacent to "
"AP HS and enemy units Threaten AP HS, switch to Defense Posture for this "
"movement. Otherwise:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3730
msgid ""
"1. Attack a Colony: This turn, attack a Colony or HW, preferring Player-"
"owned colonies over NPA. If the only eligible hex is in or through a "
"Black Hole, roll 1d10. On a 10, the fleet attacks through/into the Black "
"Hole. If a HW is among eligible Colonies this turn, make a Paranoia "
"Check. On a Pass, attack the HW. On a Fail, attack a colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3731
msgid ""
"2. Attack a Fleet: This turn, attack a hex containing Player ships. If "
"the only eligible hex is in or through a Black Hole, roll 1d10. On a 10, "
"the fleet attacks through/into the Black Hole."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3732
msgid ""
"3. Advance: Select the nearest enemy colony (NPA or human) that can be "
"reached through an explored path. The destination hex is such that it "
"brings the fleet to the colony along the fastest explored route."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3733
msgid ""
"4. Merge with Friendly Fleet: This turn, move to the strongest (in terms "
"of allocated CP) friendly Expansion/ Extermination fleet. See Merging AP "
"Fleets below."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3734
msgid ""
"5. Restrictions and Priorities: Expansion fleets avoid moving into the GC"
" and only consider attacking a Player HW as per Attack a Colony above. If"
" the current Strategy is Raiders, SC Rush or Fighters, this Fleet is "
"forbidden from attacking or advancing towards NPA colonies. This fleet "
"prioritizes first a destination hex with other friendly attacking fleets,"
" second a destination without Threat, third a destination that brings it "
"closer to an enemy colony. If eligible destination hexes include "
"Threatened Detrimental Terrain, make a Paranoia Check, on a fail, the "
"fleet will not enter Detrimental Terrain. On a pass it will be able to "
"enter."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3735 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3780
msgid "• Destination Check (Defense):"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3736
msgid ""
"1. Defend: This turn, attack or move closer to enemy ships Threatening "
"first AP HW, then colonies (prioritizing those closest to HW), then "
"colony ships, then any AP HS hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3737
msgid ""
"2. Fall Back: Move towards the AP HW along a previously explored route "
"favoring the safest path. This fleet will move less than its full "
"complement of movement (or remain stationary) in a given turn if it can "
"stop at a “choke point”. A choke point represents any defensible hex by "
"which the enemy has a limited or more arduous path of entry, and the AP "
"could potentially receive timely reinforcements or an advantage in "
"combat. If enemy units are equal to or closer to AP HW than the choke "
"point, ignore the choke point."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3738
msgid ""
"3. Restrictions and Priorities: Prioritize first a destination with other"
" friendly attacking fleets, second a destination that permits Reaction "
"Movement, third a destination that brings it closer to an enemy colony. "
"If eligible destination hexes include Threatened Detrimental Terrain and "
"are in AP HS,"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3739
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 41"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3740
msgid ""
"it will be able to enter. Otherwise, make a Paranoia Check, on a fail, "
"the fleet will not enter Detrimental Terrain. On a pass it will be able "
"to enter."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3748
msgid ""
"• These are killer Fleets designed to eliminate the Player HW or GC (if "
"used)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3750
msgid "1. Attack HW/GC: This turn, attack the targeted HW/GC."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3751
msgid ""
"2. Shell Game: If no current Shell Game underway, and this is an Unknown "
"Fleet and there is more than one separate route to the targeted HW/GC, "
"the Extermination Fleet attempts a Shell Game by deploying face-down "
"Decoys. A separate route is one such that a second Fleet on advancing on "
"Offense leaving the current hex could reach the target ending each of its"
" movements in a separate hex from this current Fleet as it also advances."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3752
msgid "To start a Shell Game:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3753
msgid ""
"▪ Place one face-down ship marker in the Fleet’s hex for each separate "
"route to target. Only one of these face down markers is the real fleet, "
"the remaining markers, including possibly the original fleet marker, are "
"Decoys and follow the usual Decoy rules when revealed. For each marker "
"placed subtract 1 CP from this Fleet’s budget. The Decoys do not count as"
" a fleet for AP Maintenance."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3754
msgid ""
"▪ Treat each face-down ship marker individually for Destination "
"Selection. Meaning these face-down markers may wind up selecting "
"different target HW/ GC hexes so long as all face-down markers follow "
"different routes."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3755
msgid ""
"▪ When a face-down marker associated with this Extermination Fleet is "
"revealed, roll randomly to determine if it is a Decoy or the real "
"Extermination Fleet (i.e. if three face-down ship markers are part of "
"this shell game, a roll of 1-3 represents the real Fleet, a roll of 4-6 "
"is one Decoy, 7-9 the other Decoy, 10 re-roll). This may occur if a "
"possible Decoy arrives at its destination (attacks). It is possible that "
"the first enemy marker to arrive is a Decoy."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3756
msgid ""
"▪ If all Decoys have been revealed, the Shell Game is over, and this "
"Extermination fleet is still Unknown, it may again attempt another Shell "
"Game if multiple equidistant routes exist. If the Extermination fleet is "
"revealed, the Shell Game is over, and all related Decoys are destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3757
msgid ""
"▪ Face down AP markers may use Fast if Hit and Run BC is the current "
"Strategy."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3758
msgid ""
"3. Change Target: If this fleet (or possible Shell Game decoy) is "
"equidistant in terms of number of hexes from multiple HW/GCs, roll 1d10. "
"On a 9 or 10, this fleet (and only this fleet) changes to a different "
"HW/GC target. Then Advance."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3759
msgid ""
"4. Advance: Select a destination hex that brings this fleet closer to the"
" current target."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3760
msgid ""
"5. Exploration: If while Advancing, this fleet cannot get closer to "
"target due to unexplored DS markers and this fleet is adjacent to an "
"unexplored DS marker, this fleet reveals an unexplored DS marker as if it"
" had Exploration technology. This occurs regardless of whether or not "
"Exploration is researched. If the latter occurs, subtract 6 CP from Fleet"
" allotment or, if Known Fleet, from the budget column. If multiple "
"eligible DS markers may be revealed in this way, select the one closest "
"to target HW/GC. This Fleet will not move this turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3761
msgid ""
"6. Restrictions and Priorities: Extermination Fleets avoid NPA planets. "
"First prioritize a destination with other friendly attacking fleets, "
"second a destination without Threat, third a destination that brings it "
"closer to the targeted HW/GC. If eligible destination hexes include "
"Threatened Detrimental Terrain, make a Paranoia Check, on a fail, the "
"fleet will not enter Detrimental Terrain. On a pass it will be able to "
"enter."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3762
msgid "• Destination Check (Defense)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3763
msgid ""
"1. Defend: This turn, attack or move closer to enemy ships Threatening "
"first AP HW, then colonies (prioritizing those closest to HW), then "
"colony ships, then any AP HS hex. If none of the above are Threatened, "
"check Attack HW/GC and then Advance as per Offense Posture."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3764
msgid ""
"2. Restrictions and Priorities: First prioritize a destination with other"
" friendly attacking fleets, second a destination that permits Reaction "
"Movement, third a destination that brings it closer to target HW/GC. If "
"eligible destinations include Threatened Detrimental Terrain and are in "
"AP HS, it will be able to enter. Otherwise, make a Paranoia Check, on a "
"fail, the fleet will not enter Detrimental Terrain. On a pass it will be "
"able to enter."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3770
msgid "Guard Fleets"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3772
msgid ""
"• These are fleets that defend conquered colonies (see 13.54 for how they"
" are created). Guard Fleets do add to Maintenance for the AP but do not "
"count for Fleet Launching purposes."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3773
msgid "• Destination Check (Offense):"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3774
msgid "1. Attack a Fleet: This turn, attack a hex containing Player ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3775
msgid ""
"2. Merge with Friendly Fleet: This turn, move to the strongest (in terms "
"of allocated CP) friendly Expansion/ Extermination fleet. These ships "
"(whether face up or face down) are now part of this fleet and this Guard "
"Fleet is disbanded. If face down, they will remain face down until"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3776
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 42"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3777
msgid ""
"the fleet they merged with encounters an enemy, and then they will be "
"generated as per Strategy."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3778
msgid ""
"3. Switch to Defense: If none of the above checks are possible, switch to"
" Defense Posture."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3779
msgid ""
"4. Restrictions and Priorities: First prioritize a destination with other"
" friendly attacking fleets, second a destination without Threat, third a "
"destination that keeps it closest to its starting hex. If eligible "
"destinations include Threatened Detrimental Terrain, make a Paranoia "
"Check, on a fail, the fleet will not enter Detrimental Terrain. On a pass"
" it will be able to enter."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3781
msgid ""
"1. Defend: Move to nearest friendly colony. If at friendly colony, remain"
" stationary."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3782
msgid ""
"2. Restrictions and Priorities: First prioritize a destination that gets "
"it closer to the nearest friendly colony, then a destination with other "
"friendly attacking fleets and then a destination without Threat. If "
"eligible destinations include Threatened Detrimental Terrain, make a "
"Paranoia Check, on a fail, the fleet will not enter Detrimental Terrain. "
"On a pass it will be able to enter."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3790
msgid ""
"• The AP is capable of reaction movement (see above). AP Fleets in AP HS "
"will always react if able, unless the destination is a Black Hole or is "
"forbidden under Identify Detrimental Terrain above. AP Fleets elsewhere "
"may or may not react. If eligible destinations include Threatened "
"Detrimental Terrain, make a Paranoia Check, on a fail, the fleet will not"
" enter Detrimental Terrain. On a pass it will be able to enter."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3796
msgid "Merging AP Fleets"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3798
msgid ""
"• If two or more Unknown AP Fleets end their movement in the same hex, "
"they will merge to become a combined fleet, combining their CP. This "
"occurs before combat resolution. If, after any combat, the resulting "
"unknown AP Fleet is at least 120 CP, this is now an Extermination Fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3799
msgid ""
"• Known AP Fleets normally do not merge, unless Shattered. If this occurs"
" with an Unknown AP Fleet, add the Shattered Fleet’s CP value of ships to"
" the Unknown Fleet’s allocation. If this occurs with a Known AP Fleet, "
"just add the ships to the stack of ships already in the fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3800
msgid "• Merged Fleets use the lowest Move technology among the merging Fleets."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3801
msgid ""
"• Merging Unknown AP Fleets with differing levels of Crew Experience sets"
" their Crew Experience level to one level lower than the highest present "
"among merging Fleets, if in use."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3807
msgid "Shattered AP Fleets"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3809
msgid ""
"• Known or Unknown, non-Guard AP Fleets with less than 30 CP worth of "
"ships are considered Shattered. This status supersedes any other posture "
"or fleet type."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3810
msgid ""
"• Shattered AP Fleets move to the closest friendly fleet or FOB and will "
"merge as above taking the safest possible explored path."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3811
msgid ""
"• Unlike Guard Fleets, Shattered AP Fleets do not add to Maintenance for "
"the AP. They do not count for Fleet Launching purposes."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3817
msgid "AP Unknown Fleet Generation"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3819
msgid ""
"• Alien Technology Cards: All facedown Alien Technology cards are "
"revealed at this time, regardless of what the card says."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3820
msgid ""
"• Empire Advantages: The AP’s Empire Advantage is revealed at this time, "
"regardless of what the card says."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3821
msgid ""
"• Unknown Fleet Encounter: When an Unknown AP Fleet is encountered by a "
"human player, make a Paranoia check then technology and ships are "
"generated based on AP’s Strategy. Unknown Guard and Shattered Fleets do "
"not trigger this Paranoia check. The AP’s Strategy may change on AP "
"Unknown Fleet Generation based on Paranoia Check. The AP automatically "
"fails the Paranoia Check if this is the first Unknown Fleet generated for"
" this AP, but without Resetting Paranoia. This occurs if the first "
"encounter is an FOB alone, but only Technology will be purchased per "
"Strategy. Ships are purchased from this AP Fleet’s allotment and "
"Technology is purchased from the Technology budget. Generated ships are "
"automatically equipped with the technology just purchased. When using "
"Raider strategy, the fleets are always fully generated before any Raider "
"ships decide to remain cloaked (see below)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3822
msgid ""
"• Unknown AP Fleet Generation against NPA: NPA encounters do not cause a "
"Paranoia check and NPA battle cannot alter Paranoia. If an AP does not "
"yet have a Strategy and encounters an NPA, proceed with Strategy "
"selection as if the AP had failed a Paranoia check, without resetting "
"Paranoia. There are special considerations, below, for Strategy selection"
" against NPA."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3823
msgid ""
"• Paranoia Check: On a pass, no change to Strategy and Paranoia does not "
"reset. On a Fail and if the Technology budget has at least 30 CP, the AP "
"randomly selects a new strategy and Resets Paranoia. On a Fail and if the"
" Technology budget is <30 CP, resolve as if the Paranoia check was passed"
" (no change to Strategy and no resetting of Paranoia)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3824
msgid ""
"- Selecting a New Strategy: Roll 1d100 on the table below. If the AP "
"rolled the current or previously played Strategy, roll another 1d10. On a"
" 1-2 the AP selects the rolled strategy, otherwise the AP re-rolls the "
"d100 as above."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3825
msgid ""
"- Certain game situations, such as Empire Advantages dictate AP Strategy "
"options (see also above for other considerations):"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3826
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 43"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3827
msgid "▪ Fighter and SC Rush are re-rolled if generating for combat with an NPA."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3828
msgid ""
"▪ If this Fleet is being generated in a Nebula (or anywhere Cloaking may "
"be canceled due to terrain effects), re-roll Raiders."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3829
msgid ""
"- If the AP is playing as Alternate Empire: Replace Yarr! with Missile "
"Boats. Purchasing changes are detailed below. Special Ability counters "
"are drawn when the appropriate ship is built."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3830
msgid "- Empire Advantages:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3831
msgid "▪ Expert Tacticians: Ignore “Yarr!”"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3832
msgid "▪ Cloaking Geniuses: “Yarr!” also counts as Raiders."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3833
msgid "▪ And We Still Carry Swords: 71 to 95 is “Yarr!”, 96-100 is Raiders."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3834
msgid "▪ Star Wolves: Hit and Run BC also counts as Fighters"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3835
msgid "▪ Giant Race: “Yarr!” also counts as Biggest Ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3836
msgid "▪ Horsemen of the Plains: 41-75 is Hit and Run BC. 76-80 is Raiders."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3842
msgid "Strategy Table"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3844
msgid "1d100 Strategy"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3845 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3861
msgid "1-15"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3847
msgid "16-30"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3849 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3863
msgid "31-40"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3851
msgid "41-70"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3853 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3865
msgid "71-80"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3855
msgid "81-90"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3857 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3867
msgid "91-100"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3874
msgid "Special Counter Tech (SCT) Purchasing"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3876
msgid ""
"• If this AP Fleet is being generated due to fighting an NPA or if less "
"than 60 CP is in the Tech budget, skip SCT Purchasing."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3877
msgid "• If Raider Strategy and no Cloaking Geniuses, skip SCT Purchasing."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3878
msgid ""
"• If the AP has seen levels of counter-able tech, it purchases the first "
"level of a randomly eligible SCT, if able, based on what this AP has "
"seen. Then proceed to SCT Ship Purchasing."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3879
msgid ""
"• If the AP just failed it’s Unknown AP Fleet Paranoia Check attempt each"
" of the following:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3880
msgid ""
"1. If this AP has seen levels of counter-able tech, it purchases the next"
" level of a randomly eligible SCT, if able, based on what this AP has "
"seen."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3881
msgid ""
"2. If this AP has never seen a counter-able tech, it buys 1 level of an "
"already purchased SCT type. If no SCT previously purchased, roll 1d10. On"
" a 10, purchase a random SCT using the table below, selecting one at "
"random."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3882
msgid ""
"3. If an SCT is rolled that is not in play (e.g. Jammers and no-one is "
"Alternate Empire), reroll. If it is at max level of its committed SCT, "
"skip to SCT Ship Purchasing."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3883
msgid ""
"• SCT Ship Purchasing: Purchase up to the max CP listed in SCT ships "
"(e.g. SC for Point Defense, nothing for Security Forces). If this Fleet "
"is engaging face-up Player ships, purchase only the appropriate ship type"
" for countering any technology present."
msgstr ""

