#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4257
msgid ""
"• If the Player is attacking an AP Colony (DS or HS) with an unrevealed "
"FOB, the AP will deploy defenses there. The HW always counts as having an"
" unrevealed FOB when attacked."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4258
msgid ""
"- Place 1 Base or Starbase in this hex, if able. This is for free (paid "
"for when AP built FOB)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4259
msgid ""
"- If the AP can purchase Defense Satellite Networks it will purchase 1 "
"from Fleet budget."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4260
msgid ""
"• At any AP Colony (with or without an FOB), Ground Units may be present "
"to provide planetary defense. Roll 1d10. On a 9 or 10, there are 4 ground"
" units present. Otherwise, there are 2. Ground unit type is Inf or HI "
"based on technology. These were recruited for free and provided planetary"
" defense as normal."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4266
msgid "HS Defense Random Encounters"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4268
msgid ""
"• If Player ships that moved end their movement in an AP HS Hex there is "
"a chance random ships will appear here to defend. This is only checked "
"once per movement turn regardless of the number of different AP HS hexes "
"in which Player ships ended their movement."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4269
msgid ""
"- Roll 1d10. On a 9-10, AP ships appear and battle the Player ships that "
"moved. If multiple hexes contain Player ships that moved this turn, "
"select one hex among them at random, starting with hexes closest to the "
"AP HW or randomly among them if tied. The AP purchases ships based on "
"current Strategy straight from the Fleet Budget and places them in that "
"hex, fully upgraded. No technology purchasing occurs. No Paranoia check "
"occurs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4270
msgid ""
"- The max amount of CP spent on these ships is 30 plus 10 per unblockaded"
" DS colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4271
msgid ""
"- The generation of these ships can trigger Reaction movement from other "
"AP Fleets."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4272
msgid ""
"• If after the battle, AP ships remain or retreated, their CP value is "
"added back to Fleet Budget and the ships are removed from the board. They"
" are never part of a Fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4278
msgid "AP in Battle"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4280
msgid ""
"• NPA battles never alter the Paranoia track and never cause a Paranoia "
"Check."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4281
msgid ""
"• “Off Camera” NPA Battles: As an optional rule, battles between Unknown "
"AP Fleets and NPAs can be resolved with one roll, without generating the "
"AP Fleet. Thus, keeping the Players blind to the contents of that fleet "
"and speeding up the game. This ignores Fleet Strategy. This is done using"
" the table below by finding the line corresponding to the number of NPA "
"counters and the CP value of this Unknown AP Fleet. AP Fleets only attack"
" NPA planets if they have 60 or more CP but lines are included in the "
"table to account for situations in which the AP may unwillingly fight the"
" NPA (i.e. due to card effects). Procedure:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4282
msgid "- Draw NPA counters as usual but they will remain face-down."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4283
msgid ""
"- Find the row that matches this fleet’s CP and the column that matches "
"the number of NPA counters in the battle. The intersection is the number "
"needed to roll for the AP to win and the number in parenthesis is the CP "
"lost on a win."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4284
msgid ""
